113 static void reportTranslationError(MachineFunction &MF, 0
114 const TargetPassConfig &TPC, ----
115 OptimizationRemarkEmitter &ORE, ----
116 OptimizationRemarkMissed &R) { ----
117 MF.getProperties().set(MachineFunctionProperties::Property::FailedISel); 0
118 ----
119 // Print the function name explicitly if we don't have a debug location (which ----
120 // makes the diagnostic less useful) or if we're going to emit a raw error. ----
121 if (!R.getLocation().isValid() || TPC.isGlobalISelAbortEnabled()) 0
122 R << (" (in function: " + MF.getName() + ")").str(); 0
123 ----
124 if (TPC.isGlobalISelAbortEnabled()) 0
125 report_fatal_error(Twine(R.getMsg())); 0
126 else ----
127 ORE.emit(R); 0
128 } 0

187 IRTranslator::allocateVRegs(const Value &Val) { 0
188 auto VRegsIt = VMap.findVRegs(Val); 0
189 if (VRegsIt != VMap.vregs_end()) 0
190 return *VRegsIt->second; 0
191 auto *Regs = VMap.getVRegs(Val); 0
192 auto *Offsets = VMap.getOffsets(Val); 0
193 SmallVector SplitTys; 0
194 computeValueLLTs(*DL, *Val.getType(), SplitTys, 0
195 Offsets->empty() ? Offsets : nullptr); 0
196 for (unsigned i = 0; i < SplitTys.size(); ++i) 0
197 Regs->push_back(0); 0

201 ArrayRef IRTranslator::getOrCreateVRegs(const Value &Val) { 0
202 auto VRegsIt = VMap.findVRegs(Val); 0
203 if (VRegsIt != VMap.vregs_end()) 0
204 return *VRegsIt->second; 0
205 ----
206 if (Val.getType()->isVoidTy()) 0
207 return *VMap.getVRegs(Val); 0
208 ----
209 // Create entry for this type. ----
210 auto *VRegs = VMap.getVRegs(Val); 0
211 auto *Offsets = VMap.getOffsets(Val); 0
212 ----
213 assert(Val.getType()->isSized() && 0
214 "Don't know how to create an empty vreg"); ----
215 ----
216 SmallVector SplitTys; 0
217 computeValueLLTs(*DL, *Val.getType(), SplitTys, 0
218 Offsets->empty() ? Offsets : nullptr); 0
219 ----
220 if (!isa(Val)) { 0
221 for (auto Ty : SplitTys) 0
222 VRegs->push_back(MRI->createGenericVirtualRegister(Ty)); 0
223 return *VRegs; 0
224 } ----
225 ----
226 if (Val.getType()->isAggregateType()) { 0
227 // UndefValue, ConstantAggregateZero ----
228 auto &C = cast(Val); 0
229 unsigned Idx = 0; 0
230 while (auto Elt = C.getAggregateElement(Idx++)) { 0
231 auto EltRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(*Elt); 0
232 llvm::copy(EltRegs, std::back_inserter(*VRegs)); 0
233 } 0
234 } else { ----
235 assert(SplitTys.size() == 1 && "unexpectedly split LLT"); 0
236 VRegs->push_back(MRI->createGenericVirtualRegister(SplitTys[0])); 0
237 bool Success = translate(cast(Val), VRegs->front()); 0
238 if (!Success) { 0
239 OptimizationRemarkMissed R("gisel-irtranslator", "GISelFailure", ----
240 MF->getFunction().getSubprogram(), 0
241 &MF->getFunction().getEntryBlock()); 0
242 R << "unable to translate constant: " << ore::NV("Type", Val.getType()); 0
243 reportTranslationError(*MF, *TPC, *ORE, R); 0
244 return *VRegs; 0
245 } 0
246 } ----
247 ----
248 return *VRegs; 0
249 } 0

251 int IRTranslator::getOrCreateFrameIndex(const AllocaInst &AI) { 0
252 auto MapEntry = FrameIndices.find(&AI); 0
253 if (MapEntry != FrameIndices.end()) 0
254 return MapEntry->second; 0
255 ----
256 uint64_t ElementSize = DL->getTypeAllocSize(AI.getAllocatedType()); 0
257 uint64_t Size = ----
258 ElementSize * cast(AI.getArraySize())->getZExtValue(); 0
259 ----
260 // Always allocate at least one byte. ----
261 Size = std::max(Size, 1u); 0
262 ----
263 int &FI = FrameIndices[&AI]; 0
264 FI = MF->getFrameInfo().CreateStackObject(Size, AI.getAlign(), false, &AI); 0
265 return FI; 0
266 } ----

295 bool IRTranslator::translateBinaryOp(unsigned Opcode, const User &U, 0
296 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
297 // Get or create a virtual register for each value. ----
298 // Unless the value is a Constant => loadimm cst? ----
299 // or inline constant each time? ----
300 // Creation of a virtual register needs to have a size. ----
301 Register Op0 = getOrCreateVReg(*U.getOperand(0)); 0
302 Register Op1 = getOrCreateVReg(*U.getOperand(1)); 0
303 Register Res = getOrCreateVReg(U); 0
304 uint32_t Flags = 0; 0
305 if (isa(U)) { 0
306 const Instruction &I = cast(U); 0
307 Flags = MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(I); 0
308 } ----
309 ----
310 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(Opcode, {Res}, {Op0, Op1}, Flags); 0
311 return true; 0
312 } ----

331 bool IRTranslator::translateCompare(const User &U, 0
332 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
333 auto *CI = dyn_cast(&U); 0
334 Register Op0 = getOrCreateVReg(*U.getOperand(0)); 0
335 Register Op1 = getOrCreateVReg(*U.getOperand(1)); 0
336 Register Res = getOrCreateVReg(U); 0
337 CmpInst::Predicate Pred = ----
338 CI ? CI->getPredicate() : static_cast( 0
339 cast(U).getPredicate()); 0
340 if (CmpInst::isIntPredicate(Pred)) 0
341 MIRBuilder.buildICmp(Pred, Res, Op0, Op1); 0
342 else if (Pred == CmpInst::FCMP_FALSE) 0
343 MIRBuilder.buildCopy( 0
344 Res, getOrCreateVReg(*Constant::getNullValue(U.getType()))); 0
345 else if (Pred == CmpInst::FCMP_TRUE) 0
346 MIRBuilder.buildCopy( 0
347 Res, getOrCreateVReg(*Constant::getAllOnesValue(U.getType()))); 0
348 else { ----
349 uint32_t Flags = 0; 0
350 if (CI) 0
351 Flags = MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(*CI); 0
352 MIRBuilder.buildFCmp(Pred, Res, Op0, Op1, Flags); 0
353 } ----
354 ----
355 return true; 0
356 } ----

358 bool IRTranslator::translateRet(const User &U, MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { 0
359 const ReturnInst &RI = cast(U); 0
360 const Value *Ret = RI.getReturnValue(); 0
361 if (Ret && DL->getTypeStoreSize(Ret->getType()) == 0) 0
362 Ret = nullptr; 0
363 ----
364 ArrayRef VRegs; 0
365 if (Ret) 0
366 VRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(*Ret); 0
367 ----
368 Register SwiftErrorVReg = 0; 0
369 if (CLI->supportSwiftError() && SwiftError.getFunctionArg()) { 0
370 SwiftErrorVReg = SwiftError.getOrCreateVRegUseAt( 0
371 &RI, &MIRBuilder.getMBB(), SwiftError.getFunctionArg()); 0
372 } ----
373 ----
374 // The target may mess up with the insertion point, but ----
375 // this is not important as a return is the last instruction ----
376 // of the block anyway. ----
377 return CLI->lowerReturn(MIRBuilder, Ret, VRegs, FuncInfo, SwiftErrorVReg); 0
378 } ----
379 ----
380 void IRTranslator::emitBranchForMergedCondition( 0
381 const Value *Cond, MachineBasicBlock *TBB, MachineBasicBlock *FBB, ----
382 MachineBasicBlock *CurBB, MachineBasicBlock *SwitchBB, ----
383 BranchProbability TProb, BranchProbability FProb, bool InvertCond) { ----
384 // If the leaf of the tree is a comparison, merge the condition into ----
385 // the caseblock. ----
386 if (const CmpInst *BOp = dyn_cast(Cond)) { 0
387 CmpInst::Predicate Condition; ----
388 if (const ICmpInst *IC = dyn_cast(Cond)) { 0
389 Condition = InvertCond ? IC->getInversePredicate() : IC->getPredicate(); 0
390 } else { ----
391 const FCmpInst *FC = cast(Cond); 0
392 Condition = InvertCond ? FC->getInversePredicate() : FC->getPredicate(); 0
393 } ----
394 ----
395 SwitchCG::CaseBlock CB(Condition, false, BOp->getOperand(0), 0
396 BOp->getOperand(1), nullptr, TBB, FBB, CurBB, 0
397 CurBuilder->getDebugLoc(), TProb, FProb); 0
398 SL->SwitchCases.push_back(CB); 0
399 return; 0
400 } 0
401 ----
402 // Create a CaseBlock record representing this branch. ----
403 CmpInst::Predicate Pred = InvertCond ? CmpInst::ICMP_NE : CmpInst::ICMP_EQ; 0
404 SwitchCG::CaseBlock CB( ----
405 Pred, false, Cond, ConstantInt::getTrue(MF->getFunction().getContext()), 0
406 nullptr, TBB, FBB, CurBB, CurBuilder->getDebugLoc(), TProb, FProb); 0
407 SL->SwitchCases.push_back(CB); 0
408 } 0

410 static bool isValInBlock(const Value *V, const BasicBlock *BB) { 0
411 if (const Instruction *I = dyn_cast(V)) 0
412 return I->getParent() == BB; 0
413 return true; 0
414 } ----
415 ----
416 void IRTranslator::findMergedConditions( 0
417 const Value *Cond, MachineBasicBlock *TBB, MachineBasicBlock *FBB, ----
418 MachineBasicBlock *CurBB, MachineBasicBlock *SwitchBB, ----
419 Instruction::BinaryOps Opc, BranchProbability TProb, ----
420 BranchProbability FProb, bool InvertCond) { ----
421 using namespace PatternMatch; ----
422 assert((Opc == Instruction::And || Opc == Instruction::Or) && 0
423 "Expected Opc to be AND/OR"); ----
424 // Skip over not part of the tree and remember to invert op and operands at ----
425 // next level. ----
426 Value *NotCond; ----
427 if (match(Cond, m_OneUse(m_Not(m_Value(NotCond)))) && 0
428 isValInBlock(NotCond, CurBB->getBasicBlock())) { 0
429 findMergedConditions(NotCond, TBB, FBB, CurBB, SwitchBB, Opc, TProb, FProb, 0
430 !InvertCond); 0
431 return; 0
432 } ----
433 ----
434 const Instruction *BOp = dyn_cast(Cond); 0
435 const Value *BOpOp0, *BOpOp1; ----
436 // Compute the effective opcode for Cond, taking into account whether it needs ----
437 // to be inverted, e.g. ----
438 // and (not (or A, B)), C ----
439 // gets lowered as ----
440 // and (and (not A, not B), C) ----
441 Instruction::BinaryOps BOpc = (Instruction::BinaryOps)0; 0
442 if (BOp) { 0
443 BOpc = match(BOp, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(BOpOp0), m_Value(BOpOp1))) 0
444 ? Instruction::And 0
445 : (match(BOp, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(BOpOp0), m_Value(BOpOp1))) 0
446 ? Instruction::Or 0
447 : (Instruction::BinaryOps)0); ----
448 if (InvertCond) { 0
449 if (BOpc == Instruction::And) 0
450 BOpc = Instruction::Or; 0
451 else if (BOpc == Instruction::Or) 0
452 BOpc = Instruction::And; 0
453 } ----
454 } ----
455 ----
456 // If this node is not part of the or/and tree, emit it as a branch. ----
457 // Note that all nodes in the tree should have same opcode. ----
458 bool BOpIsInOrAndTree = BOpc && BOpc == Opc && BOp->hasOneUse(); 0
459 if (!BOpIsInOrAndTree || BOp->getParent() != CurBB->getBasicBlock() || 0
460 !isValInBlock(BOpOp0, CurBB->getBasicBlock()) || 0
461 !isValInBlock(BOpOp1, CurBB->getBasicBlock())) { 0
462 emitBranchForMergedCondition(Cond, TBB, FBB, CurBB, SwitchBB, TProb, FProb, 0
463 InvertCond); ----
464 return; 0
465 } ----
466 ----
467 // Create TmpBB after CurBB. ----
468 MachineFunction::iterator BBI(CurBB); 0
469 MachineBasicBlock *TmpBB = ----
470 MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(CurBB->getBasicBlock()); 0
471 CurBB->getParent()->insert(++BBI, TmpBB); 0
472 ----
473 if (Opc == Instruction::Or) { 0
474 // Codegen X | Y as: ----
475 // BB1: ----
476 // jmp_if_X TBB ----
477 // jmp TmpBB ----
478 // TmpBB: ----
479 // jmp_if_Y TBB ----
480 // jmp FBB ----
481 // ----
482 ----
483 // We have flexibility in setting Prob for BB1 and Prob for TmpBB. ----
484 // The requirement is that ----
485 // TrueProb for BB1 + (FalseProb for BB1 * TrueProb for TmpBB) ----
486 // = TrueProb for original BB. ----
487 // Assuming the original probabilities are A and B, one choice is to set ----
488 // BB1's probabilities to A/2 and A/2+B, and set TmpBB's probabilities to ----
489 // A/(1+B) and 2B/(1+B). This choice assumes that ----
490 // TrueProb for BB1 == FalseProb for BB1 * TrueProb for TmpBB. ----
491 // Another choice is to assume TrueProb for BB1 equals to TrueProb for ----
492 // TmpBB, but the math is more complicated. ----
493 ----
494 auto NewTrueProb = TProb / 2; 0
495 auto NewFalseProb = TProb / 2 + FProb; 0
496 // Emit the LHS condition. ----
497 findMergedConditions(BOpOp0, TBB, TmpBB, CurBB, SwitchBB, Opc, NewTrueProb, 0
498 NewFalseProb, InvertCond); ----
499 ----
500 // Normalize A/2 and B to get A/(1+B) and 2B/(1+B). ----
501 SmallVector Probs{TProb / 2, FProb}; 0
502 BranchProbability::normalizeProbabilities(Probs.begin(), Probs.end()); 0
503 // Emit the RHS condition into TmpBB. ----
504 findMergedConditions(BOpOp1, TBB, FBB, TmpBB, SwitchBB, Opc, Probs[0], 0
505 Probs[1], InvertCond); 0
506 } else { 0
507 assert(Opc == Instruction::And && "Unknown merge op!"); 0
508 // Codegen X & Y as: ----
509 // BB1: ----
510 // jmp_if_X TmpBB ----
511 // jmp FBB ----
512 // TmpBB: ----
513 // jmp_if_Y TBB ----
514 // jmp FBB ----
515 // ----
516 // This requires creation of TmpBB after CurBB. ----
517 ----
518 // We have flexibility in setting Prob for BB1 and Prob for TmpBB. ----
519 // The requirement is that ----
520 // FalseProb for BB1 + (TrueProb for BB1 * FalseProb for TmpBB) ----
521 // = FalseProb for original BB. ----
522 // Assuming the original probabilities are A and B, one choice is to set ----
523 // BB1's probabilities to A+B/2 and B/2, and set TmpBB's probabilities to ----
524 // 2A/(1+A) and B/(1+A). This choice assumes that FalseProb for BB1 == ----
525 // TrueProb for BB1 * FalseProb for TmpBB. ----
526 ----
527 auto NewTrueProb = TProb + FProb / 2; 0
528 auto NewFalseProb = FProb / 2; 0
529 // Emit the LHS condition. ----
530 findMergedConditions(BOpOp0, TmpBB, FBB, CurBB, SwitchBB, Opc, NewTrueProb, 0
531 NewFalseProb, InvertCond); ----
532 ----
533 // Normalize A and B/2 to get 2A/(1+A) and B/(1+A). ----
534 SmallVector Probs{TProb, FProb / 2}; 0
535 BranchProbability::normalizeProbabilities(Probs.begin(), Probs.end()); 0
536 // Emit the RHS condition into TmpBB. ----
537 findMergedConditions(BOpOp1, TBB, FBB, TmpBB, SwitchBB, Opc, Probs[0], 0
538 Probs[1], InvertCond); 0
539 } 0
540 } ----
541 ----
542 bool IRTranslator::shouldEmitAsBranches( 0
543 const std::vector &Cases) { ----
544 // For multiple cases, it's better to emit as branches. ----
545 if (Cases.size() != 2) 0
546 return true; 0
547 ----
548 // If this is two comparisons of the same values or'd or and'd together, they ----
549 // will get folded into a single comparison, so don't emit two blocks. ----
550 if ((Cases[0].CmpLHS == Cases[1].CmpLHS && 0
551 Cases[0].CmpRHS == Cases[1].CmpRHS) || 0
552 (Cases[0].CmpRHS == Cases[1].CmpLHS && 0
553 Cases[0].CmpLHS == Cases[1].CmpRHS)) { 0
554 return false; 0
555 } ----
556 ----
557 // Handle: (X != null) | (Y != null) --> (X|Y) != 0 ----
558 // Handle: (X == null) & (Y == null) --> (X|Y) == 0 ----
559 if (Cases[0].CmpRHS == Cases[1].CmpRHS && 0
560 Cases[0].PredInfo.Pred == Cases[1].PredInfo.Pred && 0
561 isa(Cases[0].CmpRHS) && 0
562 cast(Cases[0].CmpRHS)->isNullValue()) { 0
563 if (Cases[0].PredInfo.Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ && 0
564 Cases[0].TrueBB == Cases[1].ThisBB) 0
565 return false; 0
566 if (Cases[0].PredInfo.Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_NE && 0
567 Cases[0].FalseBB == Cases[1].ThisBB) 0
568 return false; 0
569 } ----
570 ----
571 return true; 0
572 } ----
573 ----
574 bool IRTranslator::translateBr(const User &U, MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { 0
575 const BranchInst &BrInst = cast(U); 0
576 auto &CurMBB = MIRBuilder.getMBB(); 0
577 auto *Succ0MBB = &getMBB(*BrInst.getSuccessor(0)); 0
578 ----
579 if (BrInst.isUnconditional()) { 0
580 // If the unconditional target is the layout successor, fallthrough. ----
581 if (OptLevel == CodeGenOpt::None || !CurMBB.isLayoutSuccessor(Succ0MBB)) 0
582 MIRBuilder.buildBr(*Succ0MBB); 0
583 ----
584 // Link successors. ----
585 for (const BasicBlock *Succ : successors(&BrInst)) 0
586 CurMBB.addSuccessor(&getMBB(*Succ)); 0
587 return true; 0
588 } ----
589 ----
590 // If this condition is one of the special cases we handle, do special stuff ----
591 // now. ----
592 const Value *CondVal = BrInst.getCondition(); 0
593 MachineBasicBlock *Succ1MBB = &getMBB(*BrInst.getSuccessor(1)); 0
594 ----
595 const auto &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
596 ----
597 // If this is a series of conditions that are or'd or and'd together, emit ----
598 // this as a sequence of branches instead of setcc's with and/or operations. ----
599 // As long as jumps are not expensive (exceptions for multi-use logic ops, ----
600 // unpredictable branches, and vector extracts because those jumps are likely ----
601 // expensive for any target), this should improve performance. ----
602 // For example, instead of something like: ----
603 // cmp A, B ----
604 // C = seteq ----
605 // cmp D, E ----
606 // F = setle ----
607 // or C, F ----
608 // jnz foo ----
609 // Emit: ----
610 // cmp A, B ----
611 // je foo ----
612 // cmp D, E ----
613 // jle foo ----
614 using namespace PatternMatch; ----
615 const Instruction *CondI = dyn_cast(CondVal); 0
616 if (!TLI.isJumpExpensive() && CondI && CondI->hasOneUse() && 0
617 !BrInst.hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_unpredictable)) { 0
618 Instruction::BinaryOps Opcode = (Instruction::BinaryOps)0; 0
619 Value *Vec; ----
620 const Value *BOp0, *BOp1; ----
621 if (match(CondI, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(BOp0), m_Value(BOp1)))) 0
622 Opcode = Instruction::And; 0
623 else if (match(CondI, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(BOp0), m_Value(BOp1)))) 0
624 Opcode = Instruction::Or; 0
625 ----
626 if (Opcode && !(match(BOp0, m_ExtractElt(m_Value(Vec), m_Value())) && 0
627 match(BOp1, m_ExtractElt(m_Specific(Vec), m_Value())))) { 0
628 findMergedConditions(CondI, Succ0MBB, Succ1MBB, &CurMBB, &CurMBB, Opcode, 0
629 getEdgeProbability(&CurMBB, Succ0MBB), ----
630 getEdgeProbability(&CurMBB, Succ1MBB), ----
631 /*InvertCond=*/false); ----
632 assert(SL->SwitchCases[0].ThisBB == &CurMBB && "Unexpected lowering!"); 0
633 ----
634 // Allow some cases to be rejected. ----
635 if (shouldEmitAsBranches(SL->SwitchCases)) { 0
636 // Emit the branch for this block. ----
637 emitSwitchCase(SL->SwitchCases[0], &CurMBB, *CurBuilder); 0
638 SL->SwitchCases.erase(SL->SwitchCases.begin()); 0
639 return true; 0
640 } ----
641 ----
642 // Okay, we decided not to do this, remove any inserted MBB's and clear ----
643 // SwitchCases. ----
644 for (unsigned I = 1, E = SL->SwitchCases.size(); I != E; ++I) 0
645 MF->erase(SL->SwitchCases[I].ThisBB); 0
646 ----
647 SL->SwitchCases.clear(); 0
648 } ----
649 } ----
650 ----
651 // Create a CaseBlock record representing this branch. ----
652 SwitchCG::CaseBlock CB(CmpInst::ICMP_EQ, false, CondVal, ----
653 ConstantInt::getTrue(MF->getFunction().getContext()), 0
654 nullptr, Succ0MBB, Succ1MBB, &CurMBB, ----
655 CurBuilder->getDebugLoc()); 0
656 ----
657 // Use emitSwitchCase to actually insert the fast branch sequence for this ----
658 // cond branch. ----
659 emitSwitchCase(CB, &CurMBB, *CurBuilder); 0
660 return true; 0
661 } 0
662 ----
663 void IRTranslator::addSuccessorWithProb(MachineBasicBlock *Src, 0
664 MachineBasicBlock *Dst, ----
665 BranchProbability Prob) { ----
666 if (!FuncInfo.BPI) { 0
667 Src->addSuccessorWithoutProb(Dst); 0
668 return; 0
669 } ----
670 if (Prob.isUnknown()) 0
671 Prob = getEdgeProbability(Src, Dst); 0
672 Src->addSuccessor(Dst, Prob); 0
673 } ----
674 ----
675 BranchProbability ----
676 IRTranslator::getEdgeProbability(const MachineBasicBlock *Src, 0
677 const MachineBasicBlock *Dst) const { ----
678 const BasicBlock *SrcBB = Src->getBasicBlock(); 0
679 const BasicBlock *DstBB = Dst->getBasicBlock(); 0
680 if (!FuncInfo.BPI) { 0
681 // If BPI is not available, set the default probability as 1 / N, where N is ----
682 // the number of successors. ----
683 auto SuccSize = std::max(succ_size(SrcBB), 1); 0
684 return BranchProbability(1, SuccSize); 0
685 } ----
686 return FuncInfo.BPI->getEdgeProbability(SrcBB, DstBB); 0
687 } ----
688 ----
689 bool IRTranslator::translateSwitch(const User &U, MachineIRBuilder &MIB) { 0
690 using namespace SwitchCG; ----
691 // Extract cases from the switch. ----
692 const SwitchInst &SI = cast(U); 0
693 BranchProbabilityInfo *BPI = FuncInfo.BPI; 0
694 CaseClusterVector Clusters; 0
695 Clusters.reserve(SI.getNumCases()); 0
696 for (const auto &I : SI.cases()) { 0
697 MachineBasicBlock *Succ = &getMBB(*I.getCaseSuccessor()); 0
698 assert(Succ && "Could not find successor mbb in mapping"); 0
699 const ConstantInt *CaseVal = I.getCaseValue(); 0
700 BranchProbability Prob = ----
701 BPI ? BPI->getEdgeProbability(SI.getParent(), I.getSuccessorIndex()) 0
702 : BranchProbability(1, SI.getNumCases() + 1); 0
703 Clusters.push_back(CaseCluster::range(CaseVal, CaseVal, Succ, Prob)); 0
704 } ----
705 ----
706 MachineBasicBlock *DefaultMBB = &getMBB(*SI.getDefaultDest()); 0
707 ----
708 // Cluster adjacent cases with the same destination. We do this at all ----
709 // optimization levels because it's cheap to do and will make codegen faster ----
710 // if there are many clusters. ----
711 sortAndRangeify(Clusters); 0
712 ----
713 MachineBasicBlock *SwitchMBB = &getMBB(*SI.getParent()); 0
714 ----
715 // If there is only the default destination, jump there directly. ----
716 if (Clusters.empty()) { 0
717 SwitchMBB->addSuccessor(DefaultMBB); 0
718 if (DefaultMBB != SwitchMBB->getNextNode()) 0
719 MIB.buildBr(*DefaultMBB); 0
720 return true; 0
721 } ----
722 ----
723 SL->findJumpTables(Clusters, &SI, DefaultMBB, nullptr, nullptr); 0
724 SL->findBitTestClusters(Clusters, &SI); 0
725 ----
726 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
727 dbgs() << "Case clusters: "; ----
728 for (const CaseCluster &C : Clusters) { ----
729 if (C.Kind == CC_JumpTable) ----
730 dbgs() << "JT:"; ----
731 if (C.Kind == CC_BitTests) ----
732 dbgs() << "BT:"; ----
733 ----
734 C.Low->getValue().print(dbgs(), true); ----
735 if (C.Low != C.High) { ----
736 dbgs() << '-'; ----
737 C.High->getValue().print(dbgs(), true); ----
738 } ----
739 dbgs() << ' '; ----
740 } ----
741 dbgs() << '\n'; ----
742 }); ----
743 ----
744 assert(!Clusters.empty()); 0
745 SwitchWorkList WorkList; 0
746 CaseClusterIt First = Clusters.begin(); 0
747 CaseClusterIt Last = Clusters.end() - 1; 0
748 auto DefaultProb = getEdgeProbability(SwitchMBB, DefaultMBB); 0
749 WorkList.push_back({SwitchMBB, First, Last, nullptr, nullptr, DefaultProb}); 0
750 ----
751 // FIXME: At the moment we don't do any splitting optimizations here like ----
752 // SelectionDAG does, so this worklist only has one entry. ----
753 while (!WorkList.empty()) { 0
754 SwitchWorkListItem W = WorkList.pop_back_val(); 0
755 if (!lowerSwitchWorkItem(W, SI.getCondition(), SwitchMBB, DefaultMBB, MIB)) 0
756 return false; 0
757 } ----
758 return true; 0
759 } 0
760 ----
761 void IRTranslator::emitJumpTable(SwitchCG::JumpTable &JT, 0
762 MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { ----
763 // Emit the code for the jump table ----
764 assert(JT.Reg != -1U && "Should lower JT Header first!"); 0
765 MachineIRBuilder MIB(*MBB->getParent()); 0
766 MIB.setMBB(*MBB); 0
767 MIB.setDebugLoc(CurBuilder->getDebugLoc()); 0
768 ----
769 Type *PtrIRTy = Type::getInt8PtrTy(MF->getFunction().getContext()); 0
770 const LLT PtrTy = getLLTForType(*PtrIRTy, *DL); 0
771 ----
772 auto Table = MIB.buildJumpTable(PtrTy, JT.JTI); 0
773 MIB.buildBrJT(Table.getReg(0), JT.JTI, JT.Reg); 0
774 } 0
775 ----
776 bool IRTranslator::emitJumpTableHeader(SwitchCG::JumpTable &JT, 0
777 SwitchCG::JumpTableHeader &JTH, ----
778 MachineBasicBlock *HeaderBB) { ----
779 MachineIRBuilder MIB(*HeaderBB->getParent()); 0
780 MIB.setMBB(*HeaderBB); 0
781 MIB.setDebugLoc(CurBuilder->getDebugLoc()); 0
782 ----
783 const Value &SValue = *JTH.SValue; 0
784 // Subtract the lowest switch case value from the value being switched on. ----
785 const LLT SwitchTy = getLLTForType(*SValue.getType(), *DL); 0
786 Register SwitchOpReg = getOrCreateVReg(SValue); 0
787 auto FirstCst = MIB.buildConstant(SwitchTy, JTH.First); 0
788 auto Sub = MIB.buildSub({SwitchTy}, SwitchOpReg, FirstCst); 0
789 ----
790 // This value may be smaller or larger than the target's pointer type, and ----
791 // therefore require extension or truncating. ----
792 Type *PtrIRTy = SValue.getType()->getPointerTo(); 0
793 const LLT PtrScalarTy = LLT::scalar(DL->getTypeSizeInBits(PtrIRTy)); 0
794 Sub = MIB.buildZExtOrTrunc(PtrScalarTy, Sub); 0
795 ----
796 JT.Reg = Sub.getReg(0); 0
797 ----
798 if (JTH.FallthroughUnreachable) { 0
799 if (JT.MBB != HeaderBB->getNextNode()) 0
800 MIB.buildBr(*JT.MBB); 0
801 return true; 0
802 } ----
803 ----
804 // Emit the range check for the jump table, and branch to the default block ----
805 // for the switch statement if the value being switched on exceeds the ----
806 // largest case in the switch. ----
807 auto Cst = getOrCreateVReg( 0
808 *ConstantInt::get(SValue.getType(), JTH.Last - JTH.First)); 0
809 Cst = MIB.buildZExtOrTrunc(PtrScalarTy, Cst).getReg(0); 0
810 auto Cmp = MIB.buildICmp(CmpInst::ICMP_UGT, LLT::scalar(1), Sub, Cst); 0
811 ----
812 auto BrCond = MIB.buildBrCond(Cmp.getReg(0), *JT.Default); 0
813 ----
814 // Avoid emitting unnecessary branches to the next block. ----
815 if (JT.MBB != HeaderBB->getNextNode()) 0
816 BrCond = MIB.buildBr(*JT.MBB); 0
817 return true; 0
818 } 0
819 ----
820 void IRTranslator::emitSwitchCase(SwitchCG::CaseBlock &CB, 0
821 MachineBasicBlock *SwitchBB, ----
822 MachineIRBuilder &MIB) { ----
823 Register CondLHS = getOrCreateVReg(*CB.CmpLHS); 0
824 Register Cond; 0
825 DebugLoc OldDbgLoc = MIB.getDebugLoc(); 0
826 MIB.setDebugLoc(CB.DbgLoc); 0
827 MIB.setMBB(*CB.ThisBB); 0
828 ----
829 if (CB.PredInfo.NoCmp) { 0
830 // Branch or fall through to TrueBB. ----
831 addSuccessorWithProb(CB.ThisBB, CB.TrueBB, CB.TrueProb); 0
832 addMachineCFGPred({SwitchBB->getBasicBlock(), CB.TrueBB->getBasicBlock()}, 0
833 CB.ThisBB); ----
834 CB.ThisBB->normalizeSuccProbs(); 0
835 if (CB.TrueBB != CB.ThisBB->getNextNode()) 0
836 MIB.buildBr(*CB.TrueBB); 0
837 MIB.setDebugLoc(OldDbgLoc); 0
838 return; 0
839 } ----
840 ----
841 const LLT i1Ty = LLT::scalar(1); 0
842 // Build the compare. ----
843 if (!CB.CmpMHS) { 0
844 const auto *CI = dyn_cast(CB.CmpRHS); 0
845 // For conditional branch lowering, we might try to do something silly like ----
846 // emit an G_ICMP to compare an existing G_ICMP i1 result with true. If so, ----
847 // just re-use the existing condition vreg. ----
848 if (MRI->getType(CondLHS).getSizeInBits() == 1 && CI && CI->isOne() && 0
849 CB.PredInfo.Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ) { 0
850 Cond = CondLHS; 0
851 } else { ----
852 Register CondRHS = getOrCreateVReg(*CB.CmpRHS); 0
853 if (CmpInst::isFPPredicate(CB.PredInfo.Pred)) 0
854 Cond = ----
855 MIB.buildFCmp(CB.PredInfo.Pred, i1Ty, CondLHS, CondRHS).getReg(0); 0
856 else ----
857 Cond = ----
858 MIB.buildICmp(CB.PredInfo.Pred, i1Ty, CondLHS, CondRHS).getReg(0); 0
859 } ----
860 } else { ----
861 assert(CB.PredInfo.Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLE && 0
862 "Can only handle SLE ranges"); ----
863 ----
864 const APInt& Low = cast(CB.CmpLHS)->getValue(); 0
865 const APInt& High = cast(CB.CmpRHS)->getValue(); 0
866 ----
867 Register CmpOpReg = getOrCreateVReg(*CB.CmpMHS); 0
868 if (cast(CB.CmpLHS)->isMinValue(true)) { 0
869 Register CondRHS = getOrCreateVReg(*CB.CmpRHS); 0
870 Cond = ----
871 MIB.buildICmp(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, i1Ty, CmpOpReg, CondRHS).getReg(0); 0
872 } else { ----
873 const LLT CmpTy = MRI->getType(CmpOpReg); 0
874 auto Sub = MIB.buildSub({CmpTy}, CmpOpReg, CondLHS); 0
875 auto Diff = MIB.buildConstant(CmpTy, High - Low); 0
876 Cond = MIB.buildICmp(CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, i1Ty, Sub, Diff).getReg(0); 0
877 } ----
878 } ----
879 ----
880 // Update successor info ----
881 addSuccessorWithProb(CB.ThisBB, CB.TrueBB, CB.TrueProb); 0
882 ----
883 addMachineCFGPred({SwitchBB->getBasicBlock(), CB.TrueBB->getBasicBlock()}, 0
884 CB.ThisBB); ----
885 ----
886 // TrueBB and FalseBB are always different unless the incoming IR is ----
887 // degenerate. This only happens when running llc on weird IR. ----
888 if (CB.TrueBB != CB.FalseBB) 0
889 addSuccessorWithProb(CB.ThisBB, CB.FalseBB, CB.FalseProb); 0
890 CB.ThisBB->normalizeSuccProbs(); 0
891 ----
892 addMachineCFGPred({SwitchBB->getBasicBlock(), CB.FalseBB->getBasicBlock()}, 0
893 CB.ThisBB); ----
894 ----
895 MIB.buildBrCond(Cond, *CB.TrueBB); 0
896 MIB.buildBr(*CB.FalseBB); 0
897 MIB.setDebugLoc(OldDbgLoc); 0
898 } 0
899 ----
900 bool IRTranslator::lowerJumpTableWorkItem(SwitchCG::SwitchWorkListItem W, 0
901 MachineBasicBlock *SwitchMBB, ----
902 MachineBasicBlock *CurMBB, ----
903 MachineBasicBlock *DefaultMBB, ----
904 MachineIRBuilder &MIB, ----
905 MachineFunction::iterator BBI, ----
906 BranchProbability UnhandledProbs, ----
907 SwitchCG::CaseClusterIt I, ----
908 MachineBasicBlock *Fallthrough, ----
909 bool FallthroughUnreachable) { ----
910 using namespace SwitchCG; ----
911 MachineFunction *CurMF = SwitchMBB->getParent(); 0
912 // FIXME: Optimize away range check based on pivot comparisons. ----
913 JumpTableHeader *JTH = &SL->JTCases[I->JTCasesIndex].first; 0
914 SwitchCG::JumpTable *JT = &SL->JTCases[I->JTCasesIndex].second; 0
915 BranchProbability DefaultProb = W.DefaultProb; 0
916 ----
917 // The jump block hasn't been inserted yet; insert it here. ----
918 MachineBasicBlock *JumpMBB = JT->MBB; 0
919 CurMF->insert(BBI, JumpMBB); 0
920 ----
921 // Since the jump table block is separate from the switch block, we need ----
922 // to keep track of it as a machine predecessor to the default block, ----
923 // otherwise we lose the phi edges. ----
924 addMachineCFGPred({SwitchMBB->getBasicBlock(), DefaultMBB->getBasicBlock()}, 0
925 CurMBB); ----
926 addMachineCFGPred({SwitchMBB->getBasicBlock(), DefaultMBB->getBasicBlock()}, 0
927 JumpMBB); ----
928 ----
929 auto JumpProb = I->Prob; 0
930 auto FallthroughProb = UnhandledProbs; 0
931 ----
932 // If the default statement is a target of the jump table, we evenly ----
933 // distribute the default probability to successors of CurMBB. Also ----
934 // update the probability on the edge from JumpMBB to Fallthrough. ----
935 for (MachineBasicBlock::succ_iterator SI = JumpMBB->succ_begin(), 0
936 SE = JumpMBB->succ_end(); 0
937 SI != SE; ++SI) { 0
938 if (*SI == DefaultMBB) { 0
939 JumpProb += DefaultProb / 2; 0
940 FallthroughProb -= DefaultProb / 2; 0
941 JumpMBB->setSuccProbability(SI, DefaultProb / 2); 0
942 JumpMBB->normalizeSuccProbs(); 0
943 } else { ----
944 // Also record edges from the jump table block to it's successors. ----
945 addMachineCFGPred({SwitchMBB->getBasicBlock(), (*SI)->getBasicBlock()}, 0
946 JumpMBB); ----
947 } ----
948 } ----
949 ----
950 if (FallthroughUnreachable) 0
951 JTH->FallthroughUnreachable = true; 0
952 ----
953 if (!JTH->FallthroughUnreachable) 0
954 addSuccessorWithProb(CurMBB, Fallthrough, FallthroughProb); 0
955 addSuccessorWithProb(CurMBB, JumpMBB, JumpProb); 0
956 CurMBB->normalizeSuccProbs(); 0
957 ----
958 // The jump table header will be inserted in our current block, do the ----
959 // range check, and fall through to our fallthrough block. ----
960 JTH->HeaderBB = CurMBB; 0
961 JT->Default = Fallthrough; // FIXME: Move Default to JumpTableHeader. 0
962 ----
963 // If we're in the right place, emit the jump table header right now. ----
964 if (CurMBB == SwitchMBB) { 0
965 if (!emitJumpTableHeader(*JT, *JTH, CurMBB)) 0
966 return false; 0
967 JTH->Emitted = true; 0
968 } ----
969 return true; 0
970 } ----
971 bool IRTranslator::lowerSwitchRangeWorkItem(SwitchCG::CaseClusterIt I, 0
972 Value *Cond, ----
973 MachineBasicBlock *Fallthrough, ----
974 bool FallthroughUnreachable, ----
975 BranchProbability UnhandledProbs, ----
976 MachineBasicBlock *CurMBB, ----
977 MachineIRBuilder &MIB, ----
978 MachineBasicBlock *SwitchMBB) { ----
979 using namespace SwitchCG; ----
980 const Value *RHS, *LHS, *MHS; ----
981 CmpInst::Predicate Pred; ----
982 if (I->Low == I->High) { 0
983 // Check Cond == I->Low. ----
984 Pred = CmpInst::ICMP_EQ; 0
985 LHS = Cond; 0
986 RHS = I->Low; 0
987 MHS = nullptr; 0
988 } else { ----
989 // Check I->Low <= Cond <= I->High. ----
990 Pred = CmpInst::ICMP_SLE; 0
991 LHS = I->Low; 0
992 MHS = Cond; 0
993 RHS = I->High; 0
994 } ----
995 ----
996 // If Fallthrough is unreachable, fold away the comparison. ----
997 // The false probability is the sum of all unhandled cases. ----
998 CaseBlock CB(Pred, FallthroughUnreachable, LHS, RHS, MHS, I->MBB, Fallthrough, 0
999 CurMBB, MIB.getDebugLoc(), I->Prob, UnhandledProbs); 0
1000 ----
1001 emitSwitchCase(CB, SwitchMBB, MIB); 0
1002 return true; 0
1003 } 0
1004 ----
1005 void IRTranslator::emitBitTestHeader(SwitchCG::BitTestBlock &B, 0
1006 MachineBasicBlock *SwitchBB) { ----
1007 MachineIRBuilder &MIB = *CurBuilder; 0
1008 MIB.setMBB(*SwitchBB); 0
1009 ----
1010 // Subtract the minimum value. ----
1011 Register SwitchOpReg = getOrCreateVReg(*B.SValue); 0
1012 ----
1013 LLT SwitchOpTy = MRI->getType(SwitchOpReg); 0
1014 Register MinValReg = MIB.buildConstant(SwitchOpTy, B.First).getReg(0); 0
1015 auto RangeSub = MIB.buildSub(SwitchOpTy, SwitchOpReg, MinValReg); 0
1016 ----
1017 Type *PtrIRTy = Type::getInt8PtrTy(MF->getFunction().getContext()); 0
1018 const LLT PtrTy = getLLTForType(*PtrIRTy, *DL); 0
1019 ----
1020 LLT MaskTy = SwitchOpTy; 0
1021 if (MaskTy.getSizeInBits() > PtrTy.getSizeInBits() || 0
1022 !llvm::has_single_bit(MaskTy.getSizeInBits())) 0
1023 MaskTy = LLT::scalar(PtrTy.getSizeInBits()); 0
1024 else { ----
1025 // Ensure that the type will fit the mask value. ----
1026 for (unsigned I = 0, E = B.Cases.size(); I != E; ++I) { 0
1027 if (!isUIntN(SwitchOpTy.getSizeInBits(), B.Cases[I].Mask)) { 0
1028 // Switch table case range are encoded into series of masks. ----
1029 // Just use pointer type, it's guaranteed to fit. ----
1030 MaskTy = LLT::scalar(PtrTy.getSizeInBits()); 0
1031 break; 0
1032 } ----
1033 } ----
1034 } ----
1035 Register SubReg = RangeSub.getReg(0); 0
1036 if (SwitchOpTy != MaskTy) 0
1037 SubReg = MIB.buildZExtOrTrunc(MaskTy, SubReg).getReg(0); 0
1038 ----
1039 B.RegVT = getMVTForLLT(MaskTy); 0
1040 B.Reg = SubReg; 0
1041 ----
1042 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = B.Cases[0].ThisBB; 0
1043 ----
1044 if (!B.FallthroughUnreachable) 0
1045 addSuccessorWithProb(SwitchBB, B.Default, B.DefaultProb); 0
1046 addSuccessorWithProb(SwitchBB, MBB, B.Prob); 0
1047 ----
1048 SwitchBB->normalizeSuccProbs(); 0
1049 ----
1050 if (!B.FallthroughUnreachable) { 0
1051 // Conditional branch to the default block. ----
1052 auto RangeCst = MIB.buildConstant(SwitchOpTy, B.Range); 0
1053 auto RangeCmp = MIB.buildICmp(CmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_UGT, LLT::scalar(1), 0
1054 RangeSub, RangeCst); ----
1055 MIB.buildBrCond(RangeCmp, *B.Default); 0
1056 } ----
1057 ----
1058 // Avoid emitting unnecessary branches to the next block. ----
1059 if (MBB != SwitchBB->getNextNode()) 0
1060 MIB.buildBr(*MBB); 0
1061 } 0
1062 ----
1063 void IRTranslator::emitBitTestCase(SwitchCG::BitTestBlock &BB, 0
1064 MachineBasicBlock *NextMBB, ----
1065 BranchProbability BranchProbToNext, ----
1066 Register Reg, SwitchCG::BitTestCase &B, ----
1067 MachineBasicBlock *SwitchBB) { ----
1068 MachineIRBuilder &MIB = *CurBuilder; 0
1069 MIB.setMBB(*SwitchBB); 0
1070 ----
1071 LLT SwitchTy = getLLTForMVT(BB.RegVT); 0
1072 Register Cmp; 0
1073 unsigned PopCount = llvm::popcount(B.Mask); 0
1074 if (PopCount == 1) { 0
1075 // Testing for a single bit; just compare the shift count with what it ----
1076 // would need to be to shift a 1 bit in that position. ----
1077 auto MaskTrailingZeros = ----
1078 MIB.buildConstant(SwitchTy, llvm::countr_zero(B.Mask)); 0
1079 Cmp = ----
1080 MIB.buildICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, LLT::scalar(1), Reg, MaskTrailingZeros) 0
1081 .getReg(0); 0
1082 } else if (PopCount == BB.Range) { 0
1083 // There is only one zero bit in the range, test for it directly. ----
1084 auto MaskTrailingOnes = ----
1085 MIB.buildConstant(SwitchTy, llvm::countr_one(B.Mask)); 0
1086 Cmp = MIB.buildICmp(CmpInst::ICMP_NE, LLT::scalar(1), Reg, MaskTrailingOnes) 0
1087 .getReg(0); 0
1088 } else { ----
1089 // Make desired shift. ----
1090 auto CstOne = MIB.buildConstant(SwitchTy, 1); 0
1091 auto SwitchVal = MIB.buildShl(SwitchTy, CstOne, Reg); 0
1092 ----
1093 // Emit bit tests and jumps. ----
1094 auto CstMask = MIB.buildConstant(SwitchTy, B.Mask); 0
1095 auto AndOp = MIB.buildAnd(SwitchTy, SwitchVal, CstMask); 0
1096 auto CstZero = MIB.buildConstant(SwitchTy, 0); 0
1097 Cmp = MIB.buildICmp(CmpInst::ICMP_NE, LLT::scalar(1), AndOp, CstZero) 0
1098 .getReg(0); 0
1099 } ----
1100 ----
1101 // The branch probability from SwitchBB to B.TargetBB is B.ExtraProb. ----
1102 addSuccessorWithProb(SwitchBB, B.TargetBB, B.ExtraProb); 0
1103 // The branch probability from SwitchBB to NextMBB is BranchProbToNext. ----
1104 addSuccessorWithProb(SwitchBB, NextMBB, BranchProbToNext); 0
1105 // It is not guaranteed that the sum of B.ExtraProb and BranchProbToNext is ----
1106 // one as they are relative probabilities (and thus work more like weights), ----
1107 // and hence we need to normalize them to let the sum of them become one. ----
1108 SwitchBB->normalizeSuccProbs(); 0
1109 ----
1110 // Record the fact that the IR edge from the header to the bit test target ----
1111 // will go through our new block. Neeeded for PHIs to have nodes added. ----
1112 addMachineCFGPred({BB.Parent->getBasicBlock(), B.TargetBB->getBasicBlock()}, 0
1113 SwitchBB); ----
1114 ----
1115 MIB.buildBrCond(Cmp, *B.TargetBB); 0
1116 ----
1117 // Avoid emitting unnecessary branches to the next block. ----
1118 if (NextMBB != SwitchBB->getNextNode()) 0
1119 MIB.buildBr(*NextMBB); 0
1120 } 0
1121 ----
1122 bool IRTranslator::lowerBitTestWorkItem( 0
1123 SwitchCG::SwitchWorkListItem W, MachineBasicBlock *SwitchMBB, ----
1124 MachineBasicBlock *CurMBB, MachineBasicBlock *DefaultMBB, ----
1125 MachineIRBuilder &MIB, MachineFunction::iterator BBI, ----
1126 BranchProbability DefaultProb, BranchProbability UnhandledProbs, ----
1127 SwitchCG::CaseClusterIt I, MachineBasicBlock *Fallthrough, ----
1128 bool FallthroughUnreachable) { ----
1129 using namespace SwitchCG; ----
1130 MachineFunction *CurMF = SwitchMBB->getParent(); 0
1131 // FIXME: Optimize away range check based on pivot comparisons. ----
1132 BitTestBlock *BTB = &SL->BitTestCases[I->BTCasesIndex]; 0
1133 // The bit test blocks haven't been inserted yet; insert them here. ----
1134 for (BitTestCase &BTC : BTB->Cases) 0
1135 CurMF->insert(BBI, BTC.ThisBB); 0
1136 ----
1137 // Fill in fields of the BitTestBlock. ----
1138 BTB->Parent = CurMBB; 0
1139 BTB->Default = Fallthrough; 0
1140 ----
1141 BTB->DefaultProb = UnhandledProbs; 0
1142 // If the cases in bit test don't form a contiguous range, we evenly ----
1143 // distribute the probability on the edge to Fallthrough to two ----
1144 // successors of CurMBB. ----
1145 if (!BTB->ContiguousRange) { 0
1146 BTB->Prob += DefaultProb / 2; 0
1147 BTB->DefaultProb -= DefaultProb / 2; 0
1148 } ----
1149 ----
1150 if (FallthroughUnreachable) 0
1151 BTB->FallthroughUnreachable = true; 0
1152 ----
1153 // If we're in the right place, emit the bit test header right now. ----
1154 if (CurMBB == SwitchMBB) { 0
1155 emitBitTestHeader(*BTB, SwitchMBB); 0
1156 BTB->Emitted = true; 0
1157 } ----
1158 return true; 0
1159 } ----
1160 ----
1161 bool IRTranslator::lowerSwitchWorkItem(SwitchCG::SwitchWorkListItem W, 0
1162 Value *Cond, ----
1163 MachineBasicBlock *SwitchMBB, ----
1164 MachineBasicBlock *DefaultMBB, ----
1165 MachineIRBuilder &MIB) { ----
1166 using namespace SwitchCG; ----
1167 MachineFunction *CurMF = FuncInfo.MF; 0
1168 MachineBasicBlock *NextMBB = nullptr; 0
1169 MachineFunction::iterator BBI(W.MBB); 0
1170 if (++BBI != FuncInfo.MF->end()) 0
1171 NextMBB = &*BBI; 0
1172 ----
1173 if (EnableOpts) { 0
1174 // Here, we order cases by probability so the most likely case will be ----
1175 // checked first. However, two clusters can have the same probability in ----
1176 // which case their relative ordering is non-deterministic. So we use Low ----
1177 // as a tie-breaker as clusters are guaranteed to never overlap. ----
1178 llvm::sort(W.FirstCluster, W.LastCluster + 1, 0
1179 [](const CaseCluster &a, const CaseCluster &b) { 0
1180 return a.Prob != b.Prob 0
1181 ? a.Prob > b.Prob 0
1182 : a.Low->getValue().slt(b.Low->getValue()); 0
1183 }); ----
1184 ----
1185 // Rearrange the case blocks so that the last one falls through if possible ----
1186 // without changing the order of probabilities. ----
1187 for (CaseClusterIt I = W.LastCluster; I > W.FirstCluster;) { 0
1188 --I; 0
1189 if (I->Prob > W.LastCluster->Prob) 0
1190 break; 0
1191 if (I->Kind == CC_Range && I->MBB == NextMBB) { 0
1192 std::swap(*I, *W.LastCluster); 0
1193 break; 0
1194 } ----
1195 } ----
1196 } ----
1197 ----
1198 // Compute total probability. ----
1199 BranchProbability DefaultProb = W.DefaultProb; 0
1200 BranchProbability UnhandledProbs = DefaultProb; 0
1201 for (CaseClusterIt I = W.FirstCluster; I <= W.LastCluster; ++I) 0
1202 UnhandledProbs += I->Prob; 0
1203 ----
1204 MachineBasicBlock *CurMBB = W.MBB; 0
1205 for (CaseClusterIt I = W.FirstCluster, E = W.LastCluster; I <= E; ++I) { 0
1206 bool FallthroughUnreachable = false; 0
1207 MachineBasicBlock *Fallthrough; ----
1208 if (I == W.LastCluster) { 0
1209 // For the last cluster, fall through to the default destination. ----
1210 Fallthrough = DefaultMBB; 0
1211 FallthroughUnreachable = isa( 0
1212 DefaultMBB->getBasicBlock()->getFirstNonPHIOrDbg()); 0
1213 } else { ----
1214 Fallthrough = CurMF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(CurMBB->getBasicBlock()); 0
1215 CurMF->insert(BBI, Fallthrough); 0
1216 } ----
1217 UnhandledProbs -= I->Prob; 0
1218 ----
1219 switch (I->Kind) { 0
1220 case CC_BitTests: { 0
1221 if (!lowerBitTestWorkItem(W, SwitchMBB, CurMBB, DefaultMBB, MIB, BBI, 0
1222 DefaultProb, UnhandledProbs, I, Fallthrough, ----
1223 FallthroughUnreachable)) { ----
1224 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Failed to lower bit test for switch"); 0
1225 return false; 0
1226 } ----
1227 break; 0
1228 } ----
1229 ----
1230 case CC_JumpTable: { 0
1231 if (!lowerJumpTableWorkItem(W, SwitchMBB, CurMBB, DefaultMBB, MIB, BBI, 0
1232 UnhandledProbs, I, Fallthrough, ----
1233 FallthroughUnreachable)) { ----
1234 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Failed to lower jump table"); 0
1235 return false; 0
1236 } ----
1237 break; 0
1238 } ----
1239 case CC_Range: { 0
1240 if (!lowerSwitchRangeWorkItem(I, Cond, Fallthrough, 0
1241 FallthroughUnreachable, UnhandledProbs, ----
1242 CurMBB, MIB, SwitchMBB)) { ----
1243 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Failed to lower switch range"); 0
1244 return false; 0
1245 } ----
1246 break; 0
1247 } ----
1248 } ----
1249 CurMBB = Fallthrough; 0
1250 } ----
1251 ----
1252 return true; 0
1253 } ----
1254 ----
1255 bool IRTranslator::translateIndirectBr(const User &U, 0
1256 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1257 const IndirectBrInst &BrInst = cast(U); 0
1258 ----
1259 const Register Tgt = getOrCreateVReg(*BrInst.getAddress()); 0
1260 MIRBuilder.buildBrIndirect(Tgt); 0
1261 ----
1262 // Link successors. ----
1263 SmallPtrSet AddedSuccessors; 0
1264 MachineBasicBlock &CurBB = MIRBuilder.getMBB(); 0
1265 for (const BasicBlock *Succ : successors(&BrInst)) { 0
1266 // It's legal for indirectbr instructions to have duplicate blocks in the ----
1267 // destination list. We don't allow this in MIR. Skip anything that's ----
1268 // already a successor. ----
1269 if (!AddedSuccessors.insert(Succ).second) 0
1270 continue; 0
1271 CurBB.addSuccessor(&getMBB(*Succ)); 0
1272 } ----
1273 ----
1274 return true; 0
1275 } 0
1276 ----
1277 static bool isSwiftError(const Value *V) { 0
1278 if (auto Arg = dyn_cast(V)) 0
1279 return Arg->hasSwiftErrorAttr(); 0
1280 if (auto AI = dyn_cast(V)) 0
1281 return AI->isSwiftError(); 0
1282 return false; 0
1283 } ----
1284 ----
1285 bool IRTranslator::translateLoad(const User &U, MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { 0
1286 const LoadInst &LI = cast(U); 0
1287 ----
1288 unsigned StoreSize = DL->getTypeStoreSize(LI.getType()); 0
1289 if (StoreSize == 0) 0
1290 return true; 0
1291 ----
1292 ArrayRef Regs = getOrCreateVRegs(LI); 0
1293 ArrayRef Offsets = *VMap.getOffsets(LI); 0
1294 Register Base = getOrCreateVReg(*LI.getPointerOperand()); 0
1295 AAMDNodes AAInfo = LI.getAAMetadata(); 0
1296 ----
1297 const Value *Ptr = LI.getPointerOperand(); 0
1298 Type *OffsetIRTy = DL->getIndexType(Ptr->getType()); 0
1299 LLT OffsetTy = getLLTForType(*OffsetIRTy, *DL); 0
1300 ----
1301 if (CLI->supportSwiftError() && isSwiftError(Ptr)) { 0
1302 assert(Regs.size() == 1 && "swifterror should be single pointer"); 0
1303 Register VReg = ----
1304 SwiftError.getOrCreateVRegUseAt(&LI, &MIRBuilder.getMBB(), Ptr); 0
1305 MIRBuilder.buildCopy(Regs[0], VReg); 0
1306 return true; 0
1307 } ----
1308 ----
1309 auto &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
1310 MachineMemOperand::Flags Flags = ----
1311 TLI.getLoadMemOperandFlags(LI, *DL, AC, LibInfo); 0
1312 if (AA && !(Flags & MachineMemOperand::MOInvariant)) { 0
1313 if (AA->pointsToConstantMemory( 0
1314 MemoryLocation(Ptr, LocationSize::precise(StoreSize), AAInfo))) { 0
1315 Flags |= MachineMemOperand::MOInvariant; 0
1316 } ----
1317 } ----
1318 ----
1319 const MDNode *Ranges = ----
1320 Regs.size() == 1 ? LI.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range) : nullptr; 0
1321 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Regs.size(); ++i) { 0
1322 Register Addr; 0
1323 MIRBuilder.materializePtrAdd(Addr, Base, OffsetTy, Offsets[i] / 8); 0
1324 ----
1325 MachinePointerInfo Ptr(LI.getPointerOperand(), Offsets[i] / 8); 0
1326 Align BaseAlign = getMemOpAlign(LI); 0
1327 auto MMO = MF->getMachineMemOperand( 0
1328 Ptr, Flags, MRI->getType(Regs[i]), 0
1329 commonAlignment(BaseAlign, Offsets[i] / 8), AAInfo, Ranges, 0
1330 LI.getSyncScopeID(), LI.getOrdering()); 0
1331 MIRBuilder.buildLoad(Regs[i], Addr, *MMO); 0
1332 } ----
1333 ----
1334 return true; 0
1335 } ----
1336 ----
1337 bool IRTranslator::translateStore(const User &U, MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { 0
1338 const StoreInst &SI = cast(U); 0
1339 if (DL->getTypeStoreSize(SI.getValueOperand()->getType()) == 0) 0
1340 return true; 0
1341 ----
1342 ArrayRef Vals = getOrCreateVRegs(*SI.getValueOperand()); 0
1343 ArrayRef Offsets = *VMap.getOffsets(*SI.getValueOperand()); 0
1344 Register Base = getOrCreateVReg(*SI.getPointerOperand()); 0
1345 ----
1346 Type *OffsetIRTy = DL->getIndexType(SI.getPointerOperandType()); 0
1347 LLT OffsetTy = getLLTForType(*OffsetIRTy, *DL); 0
1348 ----
1349 if (CLI->supportSwiftError() && isSwiftError(SI.getPointerOperand())) { 0
1350 assert(Vals.size() == 1 && "swifterror should be single pointer"); 0
1351 ----
1352 Register VReg = SwiftError.getOrCreateVRegDefAt(&SI, &MIRBuilder.getMBB(), 0
1353 SI.getPointerOperand()); ----
1354 MIRBuilder.buildCopy(VReg, Vals[0]); 0
1355 return true; 0
1356 } ----
1357 ----
1358 auto &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
1359 MachineMemOperand::Flags Flags = TLI.getStoreMemOperandFlags(SI, *DL); 0
1360 ----
1361 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Vals.size(); ++i) { 0
1362 Register Addr; 0
1363 MIRBuilder.materializePtrAdd(Addr, Base, OffsetTy, Offsets[i] / 8); 0
1364 ----
1365 MachinePointerInfo Ptr(SI.getPointerOperand(), Offsets[i] / 8); 0
1366 Align BaseAlign = getMemOpAlign(SI); 0
1367 auto MMO = MF->getMachineMemOperand( 0
1368 Ptr, Flags, MRI->getType(Vals[i]), 0
1369 commonAlignment(BaseAlign, Offsets[i] / 8), SI.getAAMetadata(), nullptr, 0
1370 SI.getSyncScopeID(), SI.getOrdering()); 0
1371 MIRBuilder.buildStore(Vals[i], Addr, *MMO); 0
1372 } ----
1373 return true; 0
1374 } ----
1375 ----
1376 static uint64_t getOffsetFromIndices(const User &U, const DataLayout &DL) { 0
1377 const Value *Src = U.getOperand(0); 0
1378 Type *Int32Ty = Type::getInt32Ty(U.getContext()); 0
1379 ----
1380 // getIndexedOffsetInType is designed for GEPs, so the first index is the ----
1381 // usual array element rather than looking into the actual aggregate. ----
1382 SmallVector Indices; 0
1383 Indices.push_back(ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 0)); 0
1384 ----
1385 if (const ExtractValueInst *EVI = dyn_cast(&U)) { 0
1386 for (auto Idx : EVI->indices()) 0
1387 Indices.push_back(ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, Idx)); 0
1388 } else if (const InsertValueInst *IVI = dyn_cast(&U)) { 0
1389 for (auto Idx : IVI->indices()) 0
1390 Indices.push_back(ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, Idx)); 0
1391 } else { ----
1392 for (unsigned i = 1; i < U.getNumOperands(); ++i) 0
1393 Indices.push_back(U.getOperand(i)); 0
1394 } ----
1395 ----
1396 return 8 * static_cast( 0
1397 DL.getIndexedOffsetInType(Src->getType(), Indices)); 0
1398 } 0
1399 ----
1400 bool IRTranslator::translateExtractValue(const User &U, 0
1401 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1402 const Value *Src = U.getOperand(0); 0
1403 uint64_t Offset = getOffsetFromIndices(U, *DL); 0
1404 ArrayRef SrcRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(*Src); 0
1405 ArrayRef Offsets = *VMap.getOffsets(*Src); 0
1406 unsigned Idx = llvm::lower_bound(Offsets, Offset) - Offsets.begin(); 0
1407 auto &DstRegs = allocateVRegs(U); 0
1408 ----
1409 for (unsigned i = 0; i < DstRegs.size(); ++i) 0
1410 DstRegs[i] = SrcRegs[Idx++]; 0
1411 ----
1412 return true; 0
1413 } ----
1414 ----
1415 bool IRTranslator::translateInsertValue(const User &U, 0
1416 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1417 const Value *Src = U.getOperand(0); 0
1418 uint64_t Offset = getOffsetFromIndices(U, *DL); 0
1419 auto &DstRegs = allocateVRegs(U); 0
1420 ArrayRef DstOffsets = *VMap.getOffsets(U); 0
1421 ArrayRef SrcRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(*Src); 0
1422 ArrayRef InsertedRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(*U.getOperand(1)); 0
1423 auto *InsertedIt = InsertedRegs.begin(); 0
1424 ----
1425 for (unsigned i = 0; i < DstRegs.size(); ++i) { 0
1426 if (DstOffsets[i] >= Offset && InsertedIt != InsertedRegs.end()) 0
1427 DstRegs[i] = *InsertedIt++; 0
1428 else ----
1429 DstRegs[i] = SrcRegs[i]; 0
1430 } ----
1431 ----
1432 return true; 0
1433 } ----
1434 ----
1435 bool IRTranslator::translateSelect(const User &U, 0
1436 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1437 Register Tst = getOrCreateVReg(*U.getOperand(0)); 0
1438 ArrayRef ResRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(U); 0
1439 ArrayRef Op0Regs = getOrCreateVRegs(*U.getOperand(1)); 0
1440 ArrayRef Op1Regs = getOrCreateVRegs(*U.getOperand(2)); 0
1441 ----
1442 uint32_t Flags = 0; 0
1443 if (const SelectInst *SI = dyn_cast(&U)) 0
1444 Flags = MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(*SI); 0
1445 ----
1446 for (unsigned i = 0; i < ResRegs.size(); ++i) { 0
1447 MIRBuilder.buildSelect(ResRegs[i], Tst, Op0Regs[i], Op1Regs[i], Flags); 0
1448 } ----
1449 ----
1450 return true; 0
1451 } ----
1452 ----
1453 bool IRTranslator::translateCopy(const User &U, const Value &V, 0
1454 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1455 Register Src = getOrCreateVReg(V); 0
1456 auto &Regs = *VMap.getVRegs(U); 0
1457 if (Regs.empty()) { 0
1458 Regs.push_back(Src); 0
1459 VMap.getOffsets(U)->push_back(0); 0
1460 } else { ----
1461 // If we already assigned a vreg for this instruction, we can't change that. ----
1462 // Emit a copy to satisfy the users we already emitted. ----
1463 MIRBuilder.buildCopy(Regs[0], Src); 0
1464 } ----
1465 return true; 0
1466 } ----
1467 ----
1468 bool IRTranslator::translateBitCast(const User &U, 0
1469 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1470 // If we're bitcasting to the source type, we can reuse the source vreg. ----
1471 if (getLLTForType(*U.getOperand(0)->getType(), *DL) == 0
1472 getLLTForType(*U.getType(), *DL)) { 0
1473 // If the source is a ConstantInt then it was probably created by ----
1474 // ConstantHoisting and we should leave it alone. ----
1475 if (isa(U.getOperand(0))) 0
1476 return translateCast(TargetOpcode::G_CONSTANT_FOLD_BARRIER, U, 0
1477 MIRBuilder); 0
1478 return translateCopy(U, *U.getOperand(0), MIRBuilder); 0
1479 } ----
1480 ----
1481 return translateCast(TargetOpcode::G_BITCAST, U, MIRBuilder); 0
1482 } ----
1483 ----
1484 bool IRTranslator::translateCast(unsigned Opcode, const User &U, 0
1485 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1486 Register Op = getOrCreateVReg(*U.getOperand(0)); 0
1487 Register Res = getOrCreateVReg(U); 0
1488 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(Opcode, {Res}, {Op}); 0
1489 return true; 0
1490 } ----
1491 ----
1492 bool IRTranslator::translateGetElementPtr(const User &U, 0
1493 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1494 Value &Op0 = *U.getOperand(0); 0
1495 Register BaseReg = getOrCreateVReg(Op0); 0
1496 Type *PtrIRTy = Op0.getType(); 0
1497 LLT PtrTy = getLLTForType(*PtrIRTy, *DL); 0
1498 Type *OffsetIRTy = DL->getIndexType(PtrIRTy); 0
1499 LLT OffsetTy = getLLTForType(*OffsetIRTy, *DL); 0
1500 ----
1501 // Normalize Vector GEP - all scalar operands should be converted to the ----
1502 // splat vector. ----
1503 unsigned VectorWidth = 0; 0
1504 ----
1505 // True if we should use a splat vector; using VectorWidth alone is not ----
1506 // sufficient. ----
1507 bool WantSplatVector = false; 0
1508 if (auto *VT = dyn_cast(U.getType())) { 0
1509 VectorWidth = cast(VT)->getNumElements(); 0
1510 // We don't produce 1 x N vectors; those are treated as scalars. ----
1511 WantSplatVector = VectorWidth > 1; 0
1512 } ----
1513 ----
1514 // We might need to splat the base pointer into a vector if the offsets ----
1515 // are vectors. ----
1516 if (WantSplatVector && !PtrTy.isVector()) { 0
1517 BaseReg = ----
1518 MIRBuilder ----
1519 .buildSplatVector(LLT::fixed_vector(VectorWidth, PtrTy), BaseReg) 0
1520 .getReg(0); 0
1521 PtrIRTy = FixedVectorType::get(PtrIRTy, VectorWidth); 0
1522 PtrTy = getLLTForType(*PtrIRTy, *DL); 0
1523 OffsetIRTy = DL->getIndexType(PtrIRTy); 0
1524 OffsetTy = getLLTForType(*OffsetIRTy, *DL); 0
1525 } ----
1526 ----
1527 int64_t Offset = 0; 0
1528 for (gep_type_iterator GTI = gep_type_begin(&U), E = gep_type_end(&U); 0
1529 GTI != E; ++GTI) { 0
1530 const Value *Idx = GTI.getOperand(); 0
1531 if (StructType *StTy = GTI.getStructTypeOrNull()) { 0
1532 unsigned Field = cast(Idx)->getUniqueInteger().getZExtValue(); 0
1533 Offset += DL->getStructLayout(StTy)->getElementOffset(Field); 0
1534 continue; 0
1535 } else { 0
1536 uint64_t ElementSize = DL->getTypeAllocSize(GTI.getIndexedType()); 0
1537 ----
1538 // If this is a scalar constant or a splat vector of constants, ----
1539 // handle it quickly. ----
1540 if (const auto *CI = dyn_cast(Idx)) { 0
1541 Offset += ElementSize * CI->getSExtValue(); 0
1542 continue; 0
1543 } ----
1544 ----
1545 if (Offset != 0) { 0
1546 auto OffsetMIB = MIRBuilder.buildConstant({OffsetTy}, Offset); 0
1547 BaseReg = MIRBuilder.buildPtrAdd(PtrTy, BaseReg, OffsetMIB.getReg(0)) 0
1548 .getReg(0); 0
1549 Offset = 0; 0
1550 } ----
1551 ----
1552 Register IdxReg = getOrCreateVReg(*Idx); 0
1553 LLT IdxTy = MRI->getType(IdxReg); 0
1554 if (IdxTy != OffsetTy) { 0
1555 if (!IdxTy.isVector() && WantSplatVector) { 0
1556 IdxReg = MIRBuilder.buildSplatVector( 0
1557 OffsetTy.changeElementType(IdxTy), IdxReg).getReg(0); 0
1558 } ----
1559 ----
1560 IdxReg = MIRBuilder.buildSExtOrTrunc(OffsetTy, IdxReg).getReg(0); 0
1561 } ----
1562 ----
1563 // N = N + Idx * ElementSize; ----
1564 // Avoid doing it for ElementSize of 1. ----
1565 Register GepOffsetReg; 0
1566 if (ElementSize != 1) { 0
1567 auto ElementSizeMIB = MIRBuilder.buildConstant( 0
1568 getLLTForType(*OffsetIRTy, *DL), ElementSize); 0
1569 GepOffsetReg = ----
1570 MIRBuilder.buildMul(OffsetTy, IdxReg, ElementSizeMIB).getReg(0); 0
1571 } else ----
1572 GepOffsetReg = IdxReg; 0
1573 ----
1574 BaseReg = MIRBuilder.buildPtrAdd(PtrTy, BaseReg, GepOffsetReg).getReg(0); 0
1575 } ----
1576 } ----
1577 ----
1578 if (Offset != 0) { 0
1579 auto OffsetMIB = ----
1580 MIRBuilder.buildConstant(OffsetTy, Offset); 0
1581 MIRBuilder.buildPtrAdd(getOrCreateVReg(U), BaseReg, OffsetMIB.getReg(0)); 0
1582 return true; 0
1583 } ----
1584 ----
1585 MIRBuilder.buildCopy(getOrCreateVReg(U), BaseReg); 0
1586 return true; 0
1587 } ----
1588 ----
1589 bool IRTranslator::translateMemFunc(const CallInst &CI, 0
1590 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder, ----
1591 unsigned Opcode) { ----
1592 const Value *SrcPtr = CI.getArgOperand(1); 0
1593 // If the source is undef, then just emit a nop. ----
1594 if (isa(SrcPtr)) 0
1595 return true; 0
1596 ----
1597 SmallVector SrcRegs; 0
1598 ----
1599 unsigned MinPtrSize = UINT_MAX; 0
1600 for (auto AI = CI.arg_begin(), AE = CI.arg_end(); std::next(AI) != AE; ++AI) { 0
1601 Register SrcReg = getOrCreateVReg(**AI); 0
1602 LLT SrcTy = MRI->getType(SrcReg); 0
1603 if (SrcTy.isPointer()) 0
1604 MinPtrSize = std::min(SrcTy.getSizeInBits(), MinPtrSize); 0
1605 SrcRegs.push_back(SrcReg); 0
1606 } ----
1607 ----
1608 LLT SizeTy = LLT::scalar(MinPtrSize); 0
1609 ----
1610 // The size operand should be the minimum of the pointer sizes. ----
1611 Register &SizeOpReg = SrcRegs[SrcRegs.size() - 1]; 0
1612 if (MRI->getType(SizeOpReg) != SizeTy) 0
1613 SizeOpReg = MIRBuilder.buildZExtOrTrunc(SizeTy, SizeOpReg).getReg(0); 0
1614 ----
1615 auto ICall = MIRBuilder.buildInstr(Opcode); 0
1616 for (Register SrcReg : SrcRegs) 0
1617 ICall.addUse(SrcReg); 0
1618 ----
1619 Align DstAlign; 0
1620 Align SrcAlign; 0
1621 unsigned IsVol = ----
1622 cast(CI.getArgOperand(CI.arg_size() - 1))->getZExtValue(); 0
1623 ----
1624 ConstantInt *CopySize = nullptr; 0
1625 ----
1626 if (auto *MCI = dyn_cast(&CI)) { 0
1627 DstAlign = MCI->getDestAlign().valueOrOne(); 0
1628 SrcAlign = MCI->getSourceAlign().valueOrOne(); 0
1629 CopySize = dyn_cast(MCI->getArgOperand(2)); 0
1630 } else if (auto *MCI = dyn_cast(&CI)) { 0
1631 DstAlign = MCI->getDestAlign().valueOrOne(); 0
1632 SrcAlign = MCI->getSourceAlign().valueOrOne(); 0
1633 CopySize = dyn_cast(MCI->getArgOperand(2)); 0
1634 } else if (auto *MMI = dyn_cast(&CI)) { 0
1635 DstAlign = MMI->getDestAlign().valueOrOne(); 0
1636 SrcAlign = MMI->getSourceAlign().valueOrOne(); 0
1637 CopySize = dyn_cast(MMI->getArgOperand(2)); 0
1638 } else { ----
1639 auto *MSI = cast(&CI); 0
1640 DstAlign = MSI->getDestAlign().valueOrOne(); 0
1641 } ----
1642 ----
1643 if (Opcode != TargetOpcode::G_MEMCPY_INLINE) { 0
1644 // We need to propagate the tail call flag from the IR inst as an argument. ----
1645 // Otherwise, we have to pessimize and assume later that we cannot tail call ----
1646 // any memory intrinsics. ----
1647 ICall.addImm(CI.isTailCall() ? 1 : 0); 0
1648 } ----
1649 ----
1650 // Create mem operands to store the alignment and volatile info. ----
1651 MachineMemOperand::Flags LoadFlags = MachineMemOperand::MOLoad; 0
1652 MachineMemOperand::Flags StoreFlags = MachineMemOperand::MOStore; 0
1653 if (IsVol) { 0
1654 LoadFlags |= MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile; 0
1655 StoreFlags |= MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile; 0
1656 } ----
1657 ----
1658 AAMDNodes AAInfo = CI.getAAMetadata(); 0
1659 if (AA && CopySize && 0
1660 AA->pointsToConstantMemory(MemoryLocation( 0
1661 SrcPtr, LocationSize::precise(CopySize->getZExtValue()), AAInfo))) { ----
1662 LoadFlags |= MachineMemOperand::MOInvariant; 0
1663 ----
1664 // FIXME: pointsToConstantMemory probably does not imply dereferenceable, ----
1665 // but the previous usage implied it did. Probably should check ----
1666 // isDereferenceableAndAlignedPointer. ----
1667 LoadFlags |= MachineMemOperand::MODereferenceable; 0
1668 } ----
1669 ----
1670 ICall.addMemOperand( 0
1671 MF->getMachineMemOperand(MachinePointerInfo(CI.getArgOperand(0)), 0
1672 StoreFlags, 1, DstAlign, AAInfo)); ----
1673 if (Opcode != TargetOpcode::G_MEMSET) 0
1674 ICall.addMemOperand(MF->getMachineMemOperand( 0
1675 MachinePointerInfo(SrcPtr), LoadFlags, 1, SrcAlign, AAInfo)); ----
1676 ----
1677 return true; 0
1678 } 0
1679 ----
1680 void IRTranslator::getStackGuard(Register DstReg, 0
1681 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1682 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
1683 MRI->setRegClass(DstReg, TRI->getPointerRegClass(*MF)); 0
1684 auto MIB = ----
1685 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(TargetOpcode::LOAD_STACK_GUARD, {DstReg}, {}); 0
1686 ----
1687 auto &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
1688 Value *Global = TLI.getSDagStackGuard(*MF->getFunction().getParent()); 0
1689 if (!Global) 0
1690 return; 0
1691 ----
1692 unsigned AddrSpace = Global->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace(); 0
1693 LLT PtrTy = LLT::pointer(AddrSpace, DL->getPointerSizeInBits(AddrSpace)); 0
1694 ----
1695 MachinePointerInfo MPInfo(Global); 0
1696 auto Flags = MachineMemOperand::MOLoad | MachineMemOperand::MOInvariant | 0
1697 MachineMemOperand::MODereferenceable; ----
1698 MachineMemOperand *MemRef = MF->getMachineMemOperand( 0
1699 MPInfo, Flags, PtrTy, DL->getPointerABIAlignment(AddrSpace)); 0
1700 MIB.setMemRefs({MemRef}); 0
1701 } ----
1702 ----
1703 bool IRTranslator::translateOverflowIntrinsic(const CallInst &CI, unsigned Op, 0
1704 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1705 ArrayRef ResRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(CI); 0
1706 MIRBuilder.buildInstr( 0
1707 Op, {ResRegs[0], ResRegs[1]}, 0
1708 {getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getOperand(0)), getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getOperand(1))}); 0
1709 ----
1710 return true; 0
1711 } ----
1712 ----
1713 bool IRTranslator::translateFixedPointIntrinsic(unsigned Op, const CallInst &CI, 0
1714 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1715 Register Dst = getOrCreateVReg(CI); 0
1716 Register Src0 = getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getOperand(0)); 0
1717 Register Src1 = getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getOperand(1)); 0
1718 uint64_t Scale = cast(CI.getOperand(2))->getZExtValue(); 0
1719 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(Op, {Dst}, { Src0, Src1, Scale }); 0
1720 return true; 0
1721 } ----
