1825 ----
1826 bool IRTranslator::translateSimpleIntrinsic(const CallInst &CI, 0
1827 Intrinsic::ID ID, ----
1828 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1829 ----
1830 unsigned Op = getSimpleIntrinsicOpcode(ID); 0
1831 ----
1832 // Is this a simple intrinsic? ----
1833 if (Op == Intrinsic::not_intrinsic) 0
1834 return false; 0
1835 ----
1836 // Yes. Let's translate it. ----
1837 SmallVector VRegs; 0
1838 for (const auto &Arg : CI.args()) 0
1839 VRegs.push_back(getOrCreateVReg(*Arg)); 0
1840 ----
1841 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(Op, {getOrCreateVReg(CI)}, VRegs, 0
1842 MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(CI)); 0
1843 return true; 0
1844 } 0
1845 ----
1846 // TODO: Include ConstainedOps.def when all strict instructions are defined. ----
1847 static unsigned getConstrainedOpcode(Intrinsic::ID ID) { 0
1848 switch (ID) { 0
1849 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fadd: 0
1850 return TargetOpcode::G_STRICT_FADD; 0
1851 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fsub: 0
1852 return TargetOpcode::G_STRICT_FSUB; 0
1853 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fmul: 0
1854 return TargetOpcode::G_STRICT_FMUL; 0
1855 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fdiv: 0
1856 return TargetOpcode::G_STRICT_FDIV; 0
1857 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_frem: 0
1858 return TargetOpcode::G_STRICT_FREM; 0
1859 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fma: 0
1860 return TargetOpcode::G_STRICT_FMA; 0
1861 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_sqrt: 0
1862 return TargetOpcode::G_STRICT_FSQRT; 0
1863 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_ldexp: 0
1864 return TargetOpcode::G_STRICT_FLDEXP; 0
1865 default: 0
1866 return 0; 0
1867 } ----
1868 } ----
1869 ----
1870 bool IRTranslator::translateConstrainedFPIntrinsic( 0
1871 const ConstrainedFPIntrinsic &FPI, MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1872 fp::ExceptionBehavior EB = *FPI.getExceptionBehavior(); 0
1873 ----
1874 unsigned Opcode = getConstrainedOpcode(FPI.getIntrinsicID()); 0
1875 if (!Opcode) 0
1876 return false; 0
1877 ----
1878 uint32_t Flags = MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(FPI); 0
1879 if (EB == fp::ExceptionBehavior::ebIgnore) 0
1880 Flags |= MachineInstr::NoFPExcept; 0
1881 ----
1882 SmallVector VRegs; 0
1883 VRegs.push_back(getOrCreateVReg(*FPI.getArgOperand(0))); 0
1884 if (!FPI.isUnaryOp()) 0
1885 VRegs.push_back(getOrCreateVReg(*FPI.getArgOperand(1))); 0
1886 if (FPI.isTernaryOp()) 0
1887 VRegs.push_back(getOrCreateVReg(*FPI.getArgOperand(2))); 0
1888 ----
1889 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(Opcode, {getOrCreateVReg(FPI)}, VRegs, Flags); 0
1890 return true; 0
1891 } 0
1892 ----
1893 std::optional IRTranslator::getArgPhysReg(Argument &Arg) { 0
1894 auto VRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(Arg); 0
1895 if (VRegs.size() != 1) 0
1896 return std::nullopt; 0
1897 ----
1898 // Arguments are lowered as a copy of a livein physical register. ----
1899 auto *VRegDef = MF->getRegInfo().getVRegDef(VRegs[0]); 0
1900 if (!VRegDef || !VRegDef->isCopy()) 0
1901 return std::nullopt; 0
1902 return VRegDef->getOperand(1).getReg().asMCReg(); 0
1903 } ----
1904 ----
1905 bool IRTranslator::translateIfEntryValueArgument(const DbgValueInst &DebugInst, 0
1906 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1907 auto *Arg = dyn_cast(DebugInst.getValue()); 0
1908 if (!Arg) 0
1909 return false; 0
1910 ----
1911 const DIExpression *Expr = DebugInst.getExpression(); 0
1912 if (!Expr->isEntryValue()) 0
1913 return false; 0
1914 ----
1915 std::optional PhysReg = getArgPhysReg(*Arg); 0
1916 if (!PhysReg) { 0
1917 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Dropping dbg.value: expression is entry_value but " 0
1918 "couldn't find a physical register\n" ----
1919 << DebugInst << "\n"); ----
1920 return true; 0
1921 } ----
1922 ----
1923 MIRBuilder.buildDirectDbgValue(*PhysReg, DebugInst.getVariable(), 0
1924 DebugInst.getExpression()); 0
1925 return true; 0
1926 } ----
1927 ----
1928 bool IRTranslator::translateIfEntryValueArgument( 0
1929 const DbgDeclareInst &DebugInst) { ----
1930 auto *Arg = dyn_cast(DebugInst.getAddress()); 0
1931 if (!Arg) 0
1932 return false; 0
1933 ----
1934 const DIExpression *Expr = DebugInst.getExpression(); 0
1935 if (!Expr->isEntryValue()) 0
1936 return false; 0
1937 ----
1938 std::optional PhysReg = getArgPhysReg(*Arg); 0
1939 if (!PhysReg) 0
1940 return false; 0
1941 ----
1942 MF->setVariableDbgInfo(DebugInst.getVariable(), Expr, *PhysReg, 0
1943 DebugInst.getDebugLoc()); 0
1944 return true; 0
1945 } ----
1946 ----
1947 bool IRTranslator::translateKnownIntrinsic(const CallInst &CI, Intrinsic::ID ID, 0
1948 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
1949 if (auto *MI = dyn_cast(&CI)) { 0
1950 if (ORE->enabled()) { 0
1951 if (MemoryOpRemark::canHandle(MI, *LibInfo)) { 0
1952 MemoryOpRemark R(*ORE, "gisel-irtranslator-memsize", *DL, *LibInfo); 0
1953 R.visit(MI); 0
1954 } 0
1955 } ----
1956 } ----
1957 ----
1958 // If this is a simple intrinsic (that is, we just need to add a def of ----
1959 // a vreg, and uses for each arg operand, then translate it. ----
1960 if (translateSimpleIntrinsic(CI, ID, MIRBuilder)) 0
1961 return true; 0
1962 ----
1963 switch (ID) { 0
1964 default: 0
1965 break; 0
1966 case Intrinsic::lifetime_start: 0
1967 case Intrinsic::lifetime_end: { ----
1968 // No stack colouring in O0, discard region information. ----
1969 if (MF->getTarget().getOptLevel() == CodeGenOpt::None) 0
1970 return true; 0
1971 ----
1972 unsigned Op = ID == Intrinsic::lifetime_start ? TargetOpcode::LIFETIME_START 0
1973 : TargetOpcode::LIFETIME_END; ----
1974 ----
1975 // Get the underlying objects for the location passed on the lifetime ----
1976 // marker. ----
1977 SmallVector Allocas; 0
1978 getUnderlyingObjects(CI.getArgOperand(1), Allocas); 0
1979 ----
1980 // Iterate over each underlying object, creating lifetime markers for each ----
1981 // static alloca. Quit if we find a non-static alloca. ----
1982 for (const Value *V : Allocas) { 0
1983 const AllocaInst *AI = dyn_cast(V); 0
1984 if (!AI) 0
1985 continue; 0
1986 ----
1987 if (!AI->isStaticAlloca()) 0
1988 return true; 0
1989 ----
1990 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(Op).addFrameIndex(getOrCreateFrameIndex(*AI)); 0
1991 } ----
1992 return true; 0
1993 } 0
1994 case Intrinsic::dbg_declare: { 0
1995 const DbgDeclareInst &DI = cast(CI); 0
1996 assert(DI.getVariable() && "Missing variable"); 0
1997 ----
1998 const Value *Address = DI.getAddress(); 0
1999 if (!Address || isa(Address)) { 0
2000 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Dropping debug info for " << DI << "\n"); 0
2001 return true; 0
2002 } ----
2003 ----
2004 assert(DI.getVariable()->isValidLocationForIntrinsic( 0
2005 MIRBuilder.getDebugLoc()) && ----
2006 "Expected inlined-at fields to agree"); ----
2007 auto AI = dyn_cast(Address); 0
2008 if (AI && AI->isStaticAlloca()) { 0
2009 // Static allocas are tracked at the MF level, no need for DBG_VALUE ----
2010 // instructions (in fact, they get ignored if they *do* exist). ----
2011 MF->setVariableDbgInfo(DI.getVariable(), DI.getExpression(), 0
2012 getOrCreateFrameIndex(*AI), DI.getDebugLoc()); 0
2013 return true; 0
2014 } ----
2015 ----
2016 if (translateIfEntryValueArgument(DI)) 0
2017 return true; 0
2018 ----
2019 // A dbg.declare describes the address of a source variable, so lower it ----
2020 // into an indirect DBG_VALUE. ----
2021 MIRBuilder.buildIndirectDbgValue(getOrCreateVReg(*Address), 0
2022 DI.getVariable(), DI.getExpression()); 0
2023 return true; 0
2024 } ----
2025 case Intrinsic::dbg_label: { 0
2026 const DbgLabelInst &DI = cast(CI); 0
2027 assert(DI.getLabel() && "Missing label"); 0
2028 ----
2029 assert(DI.getLabel()->isValidLocationForIntrinsic( 0
2030 MIRBuilder.getDebugLoc()) && ----
2031 "Expected inlined-at fields to agree"); ----
2032 ----
2033 MIRBuilder.buildDbgLabel(DI.getLabel()); 0
2034 return true; 0
2035 } ----
2036 case Intrinsic::vaend: 0
2037 // No target I know of cares about va_end. Certainly no in-tree target ----
2038 // does. Simplest intrinsic ever! ----
2039 return true; 0
2040 case Intrinsic::vastart: { 0
2041 auto &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
2042 Value *Ptr = CI.getArgOperand(0); 0
2043 unsigned ListSize = TLI.getVaListSizeInBits(*DL) / 8; 0
2044 ----
2045 // FIXME: Get alignment ----
2046 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(TargetOpcode::G_VASTART, {}, {getOrCreateVReg(*Ptr)}) 0
2047 .addMemOperand(MF->getMachineMemOperand(MachinePointerInfo(Ptr), 0
2048 MachineMemOperand::MOStore, ----
2049 ListSize, Align(1))); ----
2050 return true; 0
2051 } ----
2052 case Intrinsic::dbg_value: { 0
2053 // This form of DBG_VALUE is target-independent. ----
2054 const DbgValueInst &DI = cast(CI); 0
2055 const Value *V = DI.getValue(); 0
2056 assert(DI.getVariable()->isValidLocationForIntrinsic( 0
2057 MIRBuilder.getDebugLoc()) && ----
2058 "Expected inlined-at fields to agree"); ----
2059 if (!V || DI.hasArgList()) { 0
2060 // DI cannot produce a valid DBG_VALUE, so produce an undef DBG_VALUE to ----
2061 // terminate any prior location. ----
2062 MIRBuilder.buildIndirectDbgValue(0, DI.getVariable(), DI.getExpression()); 0
2063 return true; 0
2064 } ----
2065 if (const auto *CI = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
2066 MIRBuilder.buildConstDbgValue(*CI, DI.getVariable(), DI.getExpression()); 0
2067 return true; 0
2068 } ----
2069 if (auto *AI = dyn_cast(V); 0
2070 AI && AI->isStaticAlloca() && DI.getExpression()->startsWithDeref()) { 0
2071 // If the value is an alloca and the expression starts with a ----
2072 // dereference, track a stack slot instead of a register, as registers ----
2073 // may be clobbered. ----
2074 auto ExprOperands = DI.getExpression()->getElements(); 0
2075 auto *ExprDerefRemoved = ----
2076 DIExpression::get(AI->getContext(), ExprOperands.drop_front()); 0
2077 MIRBuilder.buildFIDbgValue(getOrCreateFrameIndex(*AI), DI.getVariable(), 0
2078 ExprDerefRemoved); ----
2079 return true; 0
2080 } ----
2081 if (translateIfEntryValueArgument(DI, MIRBuilder)) 0
2082 return true; 0
2083 for (Register Reg : getOrCreateVRegs(*V)) { 0
2084 // FIXME: This does not handle register-indirect values at offset 0. The ----
2085 // direct/indirect thing shouldn't really be handled by something as ----
2086 // implicit as reg+noreg vs reg+imm in the first place, but it seems ----
2087 // pretty baked in right now. ----
2088 MIRBuilder.buildDirectDbgValue(Reg, DI.getVariable(), DI.getExpression()); 0
2089 } ----
2090 return true; 0
2091 } ----
2092 case Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow: 0
2093 return translateOverflowIntrinsic(CI, TargetOpcode::G_UADDO, MIRBuilder); 0
2094 case Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow: 0
2095 return translateOverflowIntrinsic(CI, TargetOpcode::G_SADDO, MIRBuilder); 0
2096 case Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow: 0
2097 return translateOverflowIntrinsic(CI, TargetOpcode::G_USUBO, MIRBuilder); 0
2098 case Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow: 0
2099 return translateOverflowIntrinsic(CI, TargetOpcode::G_SSUBO, MIRBuilder); 0
2100 case Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow: 0
2101 return translateOverflowIntrinsic(CI, TargetOpcode::G_UMULO, MIRBuilder); 0
2102 case Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow: 0
2103 return translateOverflowIntrinsic(CI, TargetOpcode::G_SMULO, MIRBuilder); 0
2104 case Intrinsic::uadd_sat: 0
2105 return translateBinaryOp(TargetOpcode::G_UADDSAT, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2106 case Intrinsic::sadd_sat: 0
2107 return translateBinaryOp(TargetOpcode::G_SADDSAT, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2108 case Intrinsic::usub_sat: 0
2109 return translateBinaryOp(TargetOpcode::G_USUBSAT, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2110 case Intrinsic::ssub_sat: 0
2111 return translateBinaryOp(TargetOpcode::G_SSUBSAT, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2112 case Intrinsic::ushl_sat: 0
2113 return translateBinaryOp(TargetOpcode::G_USHLSAT, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2114 case Intrinsic::sshl_sat: 0
2115 return translateBinaryOp(TargetOpcode::G_SSHLSAT, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2116 case Intrinsic::umin: 0
2117 return translateBinaryOp(TargetOpcode::G_UMIN, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2118 case Intrinsic::umax: 0
2119 return translateBinaryOp(TargetOpcode::G_UMAX, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2120 case Intrinsic::smin: 0
2121 return translateBinaryOp(TargetOpcode::G_SMIN, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2122 case Intrinsic::smax: 0
2123 return translateBinaryOp(TargetOpcode::G_SMAX, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2124 case Intrinsic::abs: 0
2125 // TODO: Preserve "int min is poison" arg in GMIR? ----
2126 return translateUnaryOp(TargetOpcode::G_ABS, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2127 case Intrinsic::smul_fix: 0
2128 return translateFixedPointIntrinsic(TargetOpcode::G_SMULFIX, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2129 case Intrinsic::umul_fix: 0
2130 return translateFixedPointIntrinsic(TargetOpcode::G_UMULFIX, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2131 case Intrinsic::smul_fix_sat: 0
2132 return translateFixedPointIntrinsic(TargetOpcode::G_SMULFIXSAT, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2133 case Intrinsic::umul_fix_sat: 0
2134 return translateFixedPointIntrinsic(TargetOpcode::G_UMULFIXSAT, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2135 case Intrinsic::sdiv_fix: 0
2136 return translateFixedPointIntrinsic(TargetOpcode::G_SDIVFIX, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2137 case Intrinsic::udiv_fix: 0
2138 return translateFixedPointIntrinsic(TargetOpcode::G_UDIVFIX, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2139 case Intrinsic::sdiv_fix_sat: 0
2140 return translateFixedPointIntrinsic(TargetOpcode::G_SDIVFIXSAT, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2141 case Intrinsic::udiv_fix_sat: 0
2142 return translateFixedPointIntrinsic(TargetOpcode::G_UDIVFIXSAT, CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2143 case Intrinsic::fmuladd: { 0
2144 const TargetMachine &TM = MF->getTarget(); 0
2145 const TargetLowering &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
2146 Register Dst = getOrCreateVReg(CI); 0
2147 Register Op0 = getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(0)); 0
2148 Register Op1 = getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(1)); 0
2149 Register Op2 = getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(2)); 0
2150 if (TM.Options.AllowFPOpFusion != FPOpFusion::Strict && 0
2151 TLI.isFMAFasterThanFMulAndFAdd(*MF, 0
2152 TLI.getValueType(*DL, CI.getType()))) { 0
2153 // TODO: Revisit this to see if we should move this part of the ----
2154 // lowering to the combiner. ----
2155 MIRBuilder.buildFMA(Dst, Op0, Op1, Op2, 0
2156 MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(CI)); 0
2157 } else { ----
2158 LLT Ty = getLLTForType(*CI.getType(), *DL); 0
2159 auto FMul = MIRBuilder.buildFMul( 0
2160 Ty, Op0, Op1, MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(CI)); 0
2161 MIRBuilder.buildFAdd(Dst, FMul, Op2, 0
2162 MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(CI)); 0
2163 } ----
2164 return true; 0
2165 } ----
2166 case Intrinsic::convert_from_fp16: 0
2167 // FIXME: This intrinsic should probably be removed from the IR. ----
2168 MIRBuilder.buildFPExt(getOrCreateVReg(CI), 0
2169 getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(0)), 0
2170 MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(CI)); 0
2171 return true; 0
2172 case Intrinsic::convert_to_fp16: 0
2173 // FIXME: This intrinsic should probably be removed from the IR. ----
2174 MIRBuilder.buildFPTrunc(getOrCreateVReg(CI), 0
2175 getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(0)), 0
2176 MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(CI)); 0
2177 return true; 0
2178 case Intrinsic::frexp: { 0
2179 ArrayRef VRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(CI); 0
2180 MIRBuilder.buildFFrexp(VRegs[0], VRegs[1], 0
2181 getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(0)), 0
2182 MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(CI)); 0
2183 return true; 0
2184 } ----
2185 case Intrinsic::memcpy_inline: 0
2186 return translateMemFunc(CI, MIRBuilder, TargetOpcode::G_MEMCPY_INLINE); 0
2187 case Intrinsic::memcpy: 0
2188 return translateMemFunc(CI, MIRBuilder, TargetOpcode::G_MEMCPY); 0
2189 case Intrinsic::memmove: 0
2190 return translateMemFunc(CI, MIRBuilder, TargetOpcode::G_MEMMOVE); 0
2191 case Intrinsic::memset: 0
2192 return translateMemFunc(CI, MIRBuilder, TargetOpcode::G_MEMSET); 0
2193 case Intrinsic::eh_typeid_for: { 0
2194 GlobalValue *GV = ExtractTypeInfo(CI.getArgOperand(0)); 0
2195 Register Reg = getOrCreateVReg(CI); 0
2196 unsigned TypeID = MF->getTypeIDFor(GV); 0
2197 MIRBuilder.buildConstant(Reg, TypeID); 0
2198 return true; 0
2199 } ----
2200 case Intrinsic::objectsize: 0
2201 llvm_unreachable("llvm.objectsize.* should have been lowered already"); 0
2202 ----
2203 case Intrinsic::is_constant: 0
2204 llvm_unreachable("llvm.is.constant.* should have been lowered already"); 0
2205 ----
2206 case Intrinsic::stackguard: 0
2207 getStackGuard(getOrCreateVReg(CI), MIRBuilder); 0
2208 return true; 0
2209 case Intrinsic::stackprotector: { 0
2210 const TargetLowering &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
2211 LLT PtrTy = getLLTForType(*CI.getArgOperand(0)->getType(), *DL); 0
2212 Register GuardVal; 0
2213 if (TLI.useLoadStackGuardNode()) { 0
2214 GuardVal = MRI->createGenericVirtualRegister(PtrTy); 0
2215 getStackGuard(GuardVal, MIRBuilder); 0
2216 } else ----
2217 GuardVal = getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(0)); // The guard's value. 0
2218 ----
2219 AllocaInst *Slot = cast(CI.getArgOperand(1)); 0
2220 int FI = getOrCreateFrameIndex(*Slot); 0
2221 MF->getFrameInfo().setStackProtectorIndex(FI); 0
2222 ----
2223 MIRBuilder.buildStore( 0
2224 GuardVal, getOrCreateVReg(*Slot), ----
2225 *MF->getMachineMemOperand(MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(*MF, FI), 0
2226 MachineMemOperand::MOStore | 0
2227 MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile, ----
2228 PtrTy, Align(8))); ----
2229 return true; 0
2230 } ----
2231 case Intrinsic::stacksave: { 0
2232 // Save the stack pointer to the location provided by the intrinsic. ----
2233 Register Reg = getOrCreateVReg(CI); 0
2234 Register StackPtr = MF->getSubtarget() 0
2235 .getTargetLowering() 0
2236 ->getStackPointerRegisterToSaveRestore(); 0
2237 ----
2238 // If the target doesn't specify a stack pointer, then fall back. ----
2239 if (!StackPtr) 0
2240 return false; 0
2241 ----
2242 MIRBuilder.buildCopy(Reg, StackPtr); 0
2243 return true; 0
2244 } ----
2245 case Intrinsic::stackrestore: { 0
2246 // Restore the stack pointer from the location provided by the intrinsic. ----
2247 Register Reg = getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(0)); 0
2248 Register StackPtr = MF->getSubtarget() 0
2249 .getTargetLowering() 0
2250 ->getStackPointerRegisterToSaveRestore(); 0
2251 ----
2252 // If the target doesn't specify a stack pointer, then fall back. ----
2253 if (!StackPtr) 0
2254 return false; 0
2255 ----
2256 MIRBuilder.buildCopy(StackPtr, Reg); 0
2257 return true; 0
2258 } ----
2259 case Intrinsic::cttz: 0
2260 case Intrinsic::ctlz: { ----
2261 ConstantInt *Cst = cast(CI.getArgOperand(1)); 0
2262 bool isTrailing = ID == Intrinsic::cttz; 0
2263 unsigned Opcode = isTrailing ----
2264 ? Cst->isZero() ? TargetOpcode::G_CTTZ 0
2265 : TargetOpcode::G_CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF ----
2266 : Cst->isZero() ? TargetOpcode::G_CTLZ 0
2267 : TargetOpcode::G_CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF; 0
2268 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(Opcode, {getOrCreateVReg(CI)}, 0
2269 {getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(0))}); 0
2270 return true; 0
2271 } ----
2272 case Intrinsic::invariant_start: { 0
2273 LLT PtrTy = getLLTForType(*CI.getArgOperand(0)->getType(), *DL); 0
2274 Register Undef = MRI->createGenericVirtualRegister(PtrTy); 0
2275 MIRBuilder.buildUndef(Undef); 0
2276 return true; 0
2277 } ----
2278 case Intrinsic::invariant_end: 0
2279 return true; 0
2280 case Intrinsic::expect: 0
2281 case Intrinsic::annotation: ----
2282 case Intrinsic::ptr_annotation: ----
2283 case Intrinsic::launder_invariant_group: ----
2284 case Intrinsic::strip_invariant_group: { ----
2285 // Drop the intrinsic, but forward the value. ----
2286 MIRBuilder.buildCopy(getOrCreateVReg(CI), 0
2287 getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(0))); 0
2288 return true; 0
2289 } ----
2290 case Intrinsic::assume: 0
2291 case Intrinsic::experimental_noalias_scope_decl: ----
2292 case Intrinsic::var_annotation: ----
2293 case Intrinsic::sideeffect: ----
2294 // Discard annotate attributes, assumptions, and artificial side-effects. ----
2295 return true; 0
2296 case Intrinsic::read_volatile_register: 0
2297 case Intrinsic::read_register: { ----
2298 Value *Arg = CI.getArgOperand(0); 0
2299 MIRBuilder ----
2300 .buildInstr(TargetOpcode::G_READ_REGISTER, {getOrCreateVReg(CI)}, {}) 0
2301 .addMetadata(cast(cast(Arg)->getMetadata())); 0
2302 return true; 0
2303 } ----
2304 case Intrinsic::write_register: { 0
2305 Value *Arg = CI.getArgOperand(0); 0
2306 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(TargetOpcode::G_WRITE_REGISTER) 0
2307 .addMetadata(cast(cast(Arg)->getMetadata())) 0
2308 .addUse(getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(1))); 0
2309 return true; 0
2310 } ----
2311 case Intrinsic::localescape: { 0
2312 MachineBasicBlock &EntryMBB = MF->front(); 0
2313 StringRef EscapedName = GlobalValue::dropLLVMManglingEscape(MF->getName()); 0
2314 ----
2315 // Directly emit some LOCAL_ESCAPE machine instrs. Label assignment emission ----
2316 // is the same on all targets. ----
2317 for (unsigned Idx = 0, E = CI.arg_size(); Idx < E; ++Idx) { 0
2318 Value *Arg = CI.getArgOperand(Idx)->stripPointerCasts(); 0
2319 if (isa(Arg)) 0
2320 continue; // Skip null pointers. They represent a hole in index space. 0
2321 ----
2322 int FI = getOrCreateFrameIndex(*cast(Arg)); 0
2323 MCSymbol *FrameAllocSym = ----
2324 MF->getMMI().getContext().getOrCreateFrameAllocSymbol(EscapedName, 0
2325 Idx); ----
2326 ----
2327 // This should be inserted at the start of the entry block. ----
2328 auto LocalEscape = ----
2329 MIRBuilder.buildInstrNoInsert(TargetOpcode::LOCAL_ESCAPE) 0
2330 .addSym(FrameAllocSym) 0
2331 .addFrameIndex(FI); 0
2332 ----
2333 EntryMBB.insert(EntryMBB.begin(), LocalEscape); 0
2334 } ----
2335 ----
2336 return true; 0
2337 } ----
2338 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fadd: 0
2339 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fmul: { ----
2340 // Need to check for the reassoc flag to decide whether we want a ----
2341 // sequential reduction opcode or not. ----
2342 Register Dst = getOrCreateVReg(CI); 0
2343 Register ScalarSrc = getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(0)); 0
2344 Register VecSrc = getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(1)); 0
2345 unsigned Opc = 0; 0
2346 if (!CI.hasAllowReassoc()) { 0
2347 // The sequential ordering case. ----
2348 Opc = ID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fadd 0
2349 ? TargetOpcode::G_VECREDUCE_SEQ_FADD 0
2350 : TargetOpcode::G_VECREDUCE_SEQ_FMUL; ----
2351 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(Opc, {Dst}, {ScalarSrc, VecSrc}, 0
2352 MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(CI)); 0
2353 return true; 0
2354 } ----
2355 // We split the operation into a separate G_FADD/G_FMUL + the reduce, ----
2356 // since the associativity doesn't matter. ----
2357 unsigned ScalarOpc; ----
2358 if (ID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fadd) { 0
2359 Opc = TargetOpcode::G_VECREDUCE_FADD; 0
2360 ScalarOpc = TargetOpcode::G_FADD; 0
2361 } else { ----
2362 Opc = TargetOpcode::G_VECREDUCE_FMUL; 0
2363 ScalarOpc = TargetOpcode::G_FMUL; 0
2364 } ----
2365 LLT DstTy = MRI->getType(Dst); 0
2366 auto Rdx = MIRBuilder.buildInstr( 0
2367 Opc, {DstTy}, {VecSrc}, MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(CI)); 0
2368 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(ScalarOpc, {Dst}, {ScalarSrc, Rdx}, 0
2369 MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(CI)); 0
2370 ----
2371 return true; 0
2372 } ----
2373 case Intrinsic::trap: 0
2374 case Intrinsic::debugtrap: ----
2375 case Intrinsic::ubsantrap: { ----
2376 StringRef TrapFuncName = ----
2377 CI.getAttributes().getFnAttr("trap-func-name").getValueAsString(); 0
2378 if (TrapFuncName.empty()) 0
2379 break; // Use the default handling. 0
2380 CallLowering::CallLoweringInfo Info; 0
2381 if (ID == Intrinsic::ubsantrap) { 0
2382 Info.OrigArgs.push_back({getOrCreateVRegs(*CI.getArgOperand(0)), 0
2383 CI.getArgOperand(0)->getType(), 0}); ----
2384 } ----
2385 Info.Callee = MachineOperand::CreateES(TrapFuncName.data()); 0
2386 Info.CB = &CI; 0
2387 Info.OrigRet = {Register(), Type::getVoidTy(CI.getContext()), 0}; 0
2388 return CLI->lowerCall(MIRBuilder, Info); 0
2389 } 0
2390 case Intrinsic::fptrunc_round: { 0
2391 uint32_t Flags = MachineInstr::copyFlagsFromInstruction(CI); 0
2392 ----
2393 // Convert the metadata argument to a constant integer ----
2394 Metadata *MD = cast(CI.getArgOperand(1))->getMetadata(); 0
2395 std::optional RoundMode = ----
2396 convertStrToRoundingMode(cast(MD)->getString()); 0
2397 ----
2398 // Add the Rounding mode as an integer ----
2399 MIRBuilder ----
2400 .buildInstr(TargetOpcode::G_INTRINSIC_FPTRUNC_ROUND, 0
2401 {getOrCreateVReg(CI)}, ----
2402 {getOrCreateVReg(*CI.getArgOperand(0))}, Flags) 0
2403 .addImm((int)*RoundMode); 0
2404 ----
2405 return true; 0
2406 } ----
2407 case Intrinsic::is_fpclass: { 0
2408 Value *FpValue = CI.getOperand(0); 0
2409 ConstantInt *TestMaskValue = cast(CI.getOperand(1)); 0
2410 ----
2411 MIRBuilder ----
2412 .buildInstr(TargetOpcode::G_IS_FPCLASS, {getOrCreateVReg(CI)}, 0
2413 {getOrCreateVReg(*FpValue)}) ----
2414 .addImm(TestMaskValue->getZExtValue()); 0
2415 ----
2416 return true; 0
2417 } ----
2418 #define INSTRUCTION(NAME, NARG, ROUND_MODE, INTRINSIC) \ ----
2419 case Intrinsic::INTRINSIC: ----
2420 #include "llvm/IR/ConstrainedOps.def" ----
2421 return translateConstrainedFPIntrinsic(cast(CI), 0
2422 MIRBuilder); 0
2423 ----
2424 } ----
2425 return false; 0
2426 } ----

2428 bool IRTranslator::translateInlineAsm(const CallBase &CB, 0
2429 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
2430 ----
2431 const InlineAsmLowering *ALI = MF->getSubtarget().getInlineAsmLowering(); 0
2432 ----
2433 if (!ALI) { 0
2434 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
2435 dbgs() << "Inline asm lowering is not supported for this target yet\n"); ----
2436 return false; 0
2437 } ----
2438 ----
2439 return ALI->lowerInlineAsm( 0
2440 MIRBuilder, CB, [&](const Value &Val) { return getOrCreateVRegs(Val); }); 0
2441 } ----
2442 ----
2443 bool IRTranslator::translateCallBase(const CallBase &CB, 0
2444 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
2445 ArrayRef Res = getOrCreateVRegs(CB); 0
2446 ----
2447 SmallVector, 8> Args; 0
2448 Register SwiftInVReg = 0; 0
2449 Register SwiftErrorVReg = 0; 0
2450 for (const auto &Arg : CB.args()) { 0
2451 if (CLI->supportSwiftError() && isSwiftError(Arg)) { 0
2452 assert(SwiftInVReg == 0 && "Expected only one swift error argument"); 0
2453 LLT Ty = getLLTForType(*Arg->getType(), *DL); 0
2454 SwiftInVReg = MRI->createGenericVirtualRegister(Ty); 0
2455 MIRBuilder.buildCopy(SwiftInVReg, SwiftError.getOrCreateVRegUseAt( 0
2456 &CB, &MIRBuilder.getMBB(), Arg)); 0
2457 Args.emplace_back(ArrayRef(SwiftInVReg)); 0
2458 SwiftErrorVReg = ----
2459 SwiftError.getOrCreateVRegDefAt(&CB, &MIRBuilder.getMBB(), Arg); 0
2460 continue; 0
2461 } 0
2462 Args.push_back(getOrCreateVRegs(*Arg)); 0
2463 } ----
2464 ----
2465 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast(&CB)) { 0
2466 if (ORE->enabled()) { 0
2467 if (MemoryOpRemark::canHandle(CI, *LibInfo)) { 0
2468 MemoryOpRemark R(*ORE, "gisel-irtranslator-memsize", *DL, *LibInfo); 0
2469 R.visit(CI); 0
2470 } 0
2471 } ----
2472 } ----
2473 ----
2474 // We don't set HasCalls on MFI here yet because call lowering may decide to ----
2475 // optimize into tail calls. Instead, we defer that to selection where a final ----
2476 // scan is done to check if any instructions are calls. ----
2477 bool Success = ----
2478 CLI->lowerCall(MIRBuilder, CB, Res, Args, SwiftErrorVReg, 0
2479 [&]() { return getOrCreateVReg(*CB.getCalledOperand()); }); 0
2480 ----
2481 // Check if we just inserted a tail call. ----
2482 if (Success) { 0
2483 assert(!HasTailCall && "Can't tail call return twice from block?"); 0
2484 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MF->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
2485 HasTailCall = TII->isTailCall(*std::prev(MIRBuilder.getInsertPt())); 0
2486 } ----
2487 ----
2488 return Success; 0
2489 } 0
2490 ----
2491 bool IRTranslator::translateCall(const User &U, MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { 0
2492 const CallInst &CI = cast(U); 0
2493 auto TII = MF->getTarget().getIntrinsicInfo(); 0
2494 const Function *F = CI.getCalledFunction(); 0
2495 ----
2496 // FIXME: support Windows dllimport function calls. ----
2497 if (F && (F->hasDLLImportStorageClass() || 0
2498 (MF->getTarget().getTargetTriple().isOSWindows() && 0
2499 F->hasExternalWeakLinkage()))) 0
2500 return false; 0
2501 ----
2502 // FIXME: support control flow guard targets. ----
2503 if (CI.countOperandBundlesOfType(LLVMContext::OB_cfguardtarget)) 0
2504 return false; 0
2505 ----
2506 // FIXME: support statepoints and related. ----
2507 if (isa(U)) 0
2508 return false; 0
2509 ----
2510 if (CI.isInlineAsm()) 0
2511 return translateInlineAsm(CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2512 ----
2513 diagnoseDontCall(CI); 0
2514 ----
2515 Intrinsic::ID ID = Intrinsic::not_intrinsic; 0
2516 if (F && F->isIntrinsic()) { 0
2517 ID = F->getIntrinsicID(); 0
2518 if (TII && ID == Intrinsic::not_intrinsic) 0
2519 ID = static_cast(TII->getIntrinsicID(F)); 0
2520 } ----
2521 ----
2522 if (!F || !F->isIntrinsic() || ID == Intrinsic::not_intrinsic) 0
2523 return translateCallBase(CI, MIRBuilder); 0
2524 ----
2525 assert(ID != Intrinsic::not_intrinsic && "unknown intrinsic"); 0
2526 ----
2527 if (translateKnownIntrinsic(CI, ID, MIRBuilder)) 0
2528 return true; 0
2529 ----
2530 ArrayRef ResultRegs; 0
2531 if (!CI.getType()->isVoidTy()) 0
2532 ResultRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(CI); 0
2533 ----
2534 // Ignore the callsite attributes. Backend code is most likely not expecting ----
2535 // an intrinsic to sometimes have side effects and sometimes not. ----
2536 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
2537 MIRBuilder.buildIntrinsic(ID, ResultRegs, !F->doesNotAccessMemory()); 0
2538 if (isa(CI)) 0
2539 MIB->copyIRFlags(CI); 0
2540 ----
2541 for (const auto &Arg : enumerate(CI.args())) { 0
2542 // If this is required to be an immediate, don't materialize it in a ----
2543 // register. ----
2544 if (CI.paramHasAttr(Arg.index(), Attribute::ImmArg)) { 0
2545 if (ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(Arg.value())) { 0
2546 // imm arguments are more convenient than cimm (and realistically ----
2547 // probably sufficient), so use them. ----
2548 assert(CI->getBitWidth() <= 64 && 0
2549 "large intrinsic immediates not handled"); ----
2550 MIB.addImm(CI->getSExtValue()); 0
2551 } else { ----
2552 MIB.addFPImm(cast(Arg.value())); 0
2553 } ----
2554 } else if (auto *MDVal = dyn_cast(Arg.value())) { 0
2555 auto *MD = MDVal->getMetadata(); 0
2556 auto *MDN = dyn_cast(MD); 0
2557 if (!MDN) { 0
2558 if (auto *ConstMD = dyn_cast(MD)) 0
2559 MDN = MDNode::get(MF->getFunction().getContext(), ConstMD); 0
2560 else // This was probably an MDString. ----
2561 return false; 0
2562 } ----
2563 MIB.addMetadata(MDN); 0
2564 } else { ----
2565 ArrayRef VRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(*Arg.value()); 0
2566 if (VRegs.size() > 1) 0
2567 return false; 0
2568 MIB.addUse(VRegs[0]); 0
2569 } ----
2570 } ----
2571 ----
2572 // Add a MachineMemOperand if it is a target mem intrinsic. ----
2573 const TargetLowering &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
2574 TargetLowering::IntrinsicInfo Info; 0
2575 // TODO: Add a GlobalISel version of getTgtMemIntrinsic. ----
2576 if (TLI.getTgtMemIntrinsic(Info, CI, *MF, ID)) { 0
2577 Align Alignment = Info.align.value_or( 0
2578 DL->getABITypeAlign(Info.memVT.getTypeForEVT(F->getContext()))); 0
2579 LLT MemTy = Info.memVT.isSimple() 0
2580 ? getLLTForMVT(Info.memVT.getSimpleVT()) 0
2581 : LLT::scalar(Info.memVT.getStoreSizeInBits()); 0
2582 ----
2583 // TODO: We currently just fallback to address space 0 if getTgtMemIntrinsic ----
2584 // didn't yield anything useful. ----
2585 MachinePointerInfo MPI; 0
2586 if (Info.ptrVal) 0
2587 MPI = MachinePointerInfo(Info.ptrVal, Info.offset); 0
2588 else if (Info.fallbackAddressSpace) 0
2589 MPI = MachinePointerInfo(*Info.fallbackAddressSpace); 0
2590 MIB.addMemOperand( 0
2591 MF->getMachineMemOperand(MPI, Info.flags, MemTy, Alignment, CI.getAAMetadata())); 0
2592 } ----
2593 ----
2594 return true; 0
2595 } ----
2596 ----
2597 bool IRTranslator::findUnwindDestinations( 0
2598 const BasicBlock *EHPadBB, ----
2599 BranchProbability Prob, ----
2600 SmallVectorImpl> ----
2601 &UnwindDests) { ----
2602 EHPersonality Personality = classifyEHPersonality( 0
2603 EHPadBB->getParent()->getFunction().getPersonalityFn()); 0
2604 bool IsMSVCCXX = Personality == EHPersonality::MSVC_CXX; 0
2605 bool IsCoreCLR = Personality == EHPersonality::CoreCLR; 0
2606 bool IsWasmCXX = Personality == EHPersonality::Wasm_CXX; 0
2607 bool IsSEH = isAsynchronousEHPersonality(Personality); 0
2608 ----
2609 if (IsWasmCXX) { 0
2610 // Ignore this for now. ----
2611 return false; 0
2612 } ----
2613 ----
2614 while (EHPadBB) { 0
2615 const Instruction *Pad = EHPadBB->getFirstNonPHI(); 0
2616 BasicBlock *NewEHPadBB = nullptr; 0
2617 if (isa(Pad)) { 0
2618 // Stop on landingpads. They are not funclets. ----
2619 UnwindDests.emplace_back(&getMBB(*EHPadBB), Prob); 0
2620 break; 0
2621 } ----
2622 if (isa(Pad)) { 0
2623 // Stop on cleanup pads. Cleanups are always funclet entries for all known ----
2624 // personalities. ----
2625 UnwindDests.emplace_back(&getMBB(*EHPadBB), Prob); 0
2626 UnwindDests.back().first->setIsEHScopeEntry(); 0
2627 UnwindDests.back().first->setIsEHFuncletEntry(); 0
2628 break; 0
2629 } ----
2630 if (auto *CatchSwitch = dyn_cast(Pad)) { 0
2631 // Add the catchpad handlers to the possible destinations. ----
2632 for (const BasicBlock *CatchPadBB : CatchSwitch->handlers()) { 0
2633 UnwindDests.emplace_back(&getMBB(*CatchPadBB), Prob); 0
2634 // For MSVC++ and the CLR, catchblocks are funclets and need prologues. ----
2635 if (IsMSVCCXX || IsCoreCLR) 0
2636 UnwindDests.back().first->setIsEHFuncletEntry(); 0
2637 if (!IsSEH) 0
2638 UnwindDests.back().first->setIsEHScopeEntry(); 0
2639 } ----
2640 NewEHPadBB = CatchSwitch->getUnwindDest(); 0
2641 } else { ----
2642 continue; 0
2643 } ----
2644 ----
2645 BranchProbabilityInfo *BPI = FuncInfo.BPI; 0
2646 if (BPI && NewEHPadBB) 0
2647 Prob *= BPI->getEdgeProbability(EHPadBB, NewEHPadBB); 0
2648 EHPadBB = NewEHPadBB; 0
2649 } ----
2650 return true; 0
2651 } ----
2652 ----
2653 bool IRTranslator::translateInvoke(const User &U, 0
2654 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
2655 const InvokeInst &I = cast(U); 0
2656 MCContext &Context = MF->getContext(); 0
2657 ----
2658 const BasicBlock *ReturnBB = I.getSuccessor(0); 0
2659 const BasicBlock *EHPadBB = I.getSuccessor(1); 0
2660 ----
2661 const Function *Fn = I.getCalledFunction(); 0
2662 ----
2663 // FIXME: support invoking patchpoint and statepoint intrinsics. ----
2664 if (Fn && Fn->isIntrinsic()) 0
2665 return false; 0
2666 ----
2667 // FIXME: support whatever these are. ----
2668 if (I.countOperandBundlesOfType(LLVMContext::OB_deopt)) 0
2669 return false; 0
2670 ----
2671 // FIXME: support control flow guard targets. ----
2672 if (I.countOperandBundlesOfType(LLVMContext::OB_cfguardtarget)) 0
2673 return false; 0
2674 ----
2675 // FIXME: support Windows exception handling. ----
2676 if (!isa(EHPadBB->getFirstNonPHI())) 0
2677 return false; 0
2678 ----
2679 bool LowerInlineAsm = I.isInlineAsm(); 0
2680 bool NeedEHLabel = true; 0
2681 ----
2682 // Emit the actual call, bracketed by EH_LABELs so that the MF knows about ----
2683 // the region covered by the try. ----
2684 MCSymbol *BeginSymbol = nullptr; 0
2685 if (NeedEHLabel) { 0
2686 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(TargetOpcode::G_INVOKE_REGION_START); 0
2687 BeginSymbol = Context.createTempSymbol(); 0
2688 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(TargetOpcode::EH_LABEL).addSym(BeginSymbol); 0
2689 } ----
2690 ----
2691 if (LowerInlineAsm) { 0
2692 if (!translateInlineAsm(I, MIRBuilder)) 0
2693 return false; 0
2694 } else if (!translateCallBase(I, MIRBuilder)) 0
2695 return false; 0
2696 ----
2697 MCSymbol *EndSymbol = nullptr; 0
2698 if (NeedEHLabel) { 0
2699 EndSymbol = Context.createTempSymbol(); 0
2700 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(TargetOpcode::EH_LABEL).addSym(EndSymbol); 0
2701 } ----
2702 ----
2703 SmallVector, 1> UnwindDests; 0
2704 BranchProbabilityInfo *BPI = FuncInfo.BPI; 0
2705 MachineBasicBlock *InvokeMBB = &MIRBuilder.getMBB(); 0
2706 BranchProbability EHPadBBProb = ----
2707 BPI ? BPI->getEdgeProbability(InvokeMBB->getBasicBlock(), EHPadBB) 0
2708 : BranchProbability::getZero(); 0
2709 ----
2710 if (!findUnwindDestinations(EHPadBB, EHPadBBProb, UnwindDests)) 0
2711 return false; 0
2712 ----
2713 MachineBasicBlock &EHPadMBB = getMBB(*EHPadBB), 0
2714 &ReturnMBB = getMBB(*ReturnBB); 0
2715 // Update successor info. ----
2716 addSuccessorWithProb(InvokeMBB, &ReturnMBB); 0
2717 for (auto &UnwindDest : UnwindDests) { 0
2718 UnwindDest.first->setIsEHPad(); 0
2719 addSuccessorWithProb(InvokeMBB, UnwindDest.first, UnwindDest.second); 0
2720 } ----
2721 InvokeMBB->normalizeSuccProbs(); 0
2722 ----
2723 if (NeedEHLabel) { 0
2724 assert(BeginSymbol && "Expected a begin symbol!"); 0
2725 assert(EndSymbol && "Expected an end symbol!"); 0
2726 MF->addInvoke(&EHPadMBB, BeginSymbol, EndSymbol); 0
2727 } ----
2728 ----
2729 MIRBuilder.buildBr(ReturnMBB); 0
2730 return true; 0
2731 } 0
2732 ----
2733 bool IRTranslator::translateCallBr(const User &U, 0
2734 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
2735 // FIXME: Implement this. ----
2736 return false; 0
2737 } ----
2738 ----
2739 bool IRTranslator::translateLandingPad(const User &U, 0
2740 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
2741 const LandingPadInst &LP = cast(U); 0
2742 ----
2743 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = MIRBuilder.getMBB(); 0
2744 ----
2745 MBB.setIsEHPad(); 0
2746 ----
2747 // If there aren't registers to copy the values into (e.g., during SjLj ----
2748 // exceptions), then don't bother. ----
2749 auto &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
2750 const Constant *PersonalityFn = MF->getFunction().getPersonalityFn(); 0
2751 if (TLI.getExceptionPointerRegister(PersonalityFn) == 0 && 0
2752 TLI.getExceptionSelectorRegister(PersonalityFn) == 0) 0
2753 return true; 0
2754 ----
2755 // If landingpad's return type is token type, we don't create DAG nodes ----
2756 // for its exception pointer and selector value. The extraction of exception ----
2757 // pointer or selector value from token type landingpads is not currently ----
2758 // supported. ----
2759 if (LP.getType()->isTokenTy()) 0
2760 return true; 0
2761 ----
2762 // Add a label to mark the beginning of the landing pad. Deletion of the ----
2763 // landing pad can thus be detected via the MachineModuleInfo. ----
2764 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(TargetOpcode::EH_LABEL) 0
2765 .addSym(MF->addLandingPad(&MBB)); 0
2766 ----
2767 // If the unwinder does not preserve all registers, ensure that the ----
2768 // function marks the clobbered registers as used. ----
2769 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI = *MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
2770 if (auto *RegMask = TRI.getCustomEHPadPreservedMask(*MF)) 0
2771 MF->getRegInfo().addPhysRegsUsedFromRegMask(RegMask); 0
2772 ----
2773 LLT Ty = getLLTForType(*LP.getType(), *DL); 0
2774 Register Undef = MRI->createGenericVirtualRegister(Ty); 0
2775 MIRBuilder.buildUndef(Undef); 0
2776 ----
2777 SmallVector Tys; 0
2778 for (Type *Ty : cast(LP.getType())->elements()) 0
2779 Tys.push_back(getLLTForType(*Ty, *DL)); 0
2780 assert(Tys.size() == 2 && "Only two-valued landingpads are supported"); 0
2781 ----
2782 // Mark exception register as live in. ----
2783 Register ExceptionReg = TLI.getExceptionPointerRegister(PersonalityFn); 0
2784 if (!ExceptionReg) 0
2785 return false; 0
2786 ----
2787 MBB.addLiveIn(ExceptionReg); 0
2788 ArrayRef ResRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(LP); 0
2789 MIRBuilder.buildCopy(ResRegs[0], ExceptionReg); 0
2790 ----
2791 Register SelectorReg = TLI.getExceptionSelectorRegister(PersonalityFn); 0
2792 if (!SelectorReg) 0
2793 return false; 0
2794 ----
2795 MBB.addLiveIn(SelectorReg); 0
2796 Register PtrVReg = MRI->createGenericVirtualRegister(Tys[0]); 0
2797 MIRBuilder.buildCopy(PtrVReg, SelectorReg); 0
2798 MIRBuilder.buildCast(ResRegs[1], PtrVReg); 0
2799 ----
2800 return true; 0
2801 } 0
2802 ----
2803 bool IRTranslator::translateAlloca(const User &U, 0
2804 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
2805 auto &AI = cast(U); 0
2806 ----
2807 if (AI.isSwiftError()) 0
2808 return true; 0
2809 ----
2810 if (AI.isStaticAlloca()) { 0
2811 Register Res = getOrCreateVReg(AI); 0
2812 int FI = getOrCreateFrameIndex(AI); 0
2813 MIRBuilder.buildFrameIndex(Res, FI); 0
2814 return true; 0
2815 } ----
2816 ----
2817 // FIXME: support stack probing for Windows. ----
2818 if (MF->getTarget().getTargetTriple().isOSWindows()) 0
2819 return false; 0
2820 ----
2821 // Now we're in the harder dynamic case. ----
2822 Register NumElts = getOrCreateVReg(*AI.getArraySize()); 0
2823 Type *IntPtrIRTy = DL->getIntPtrType(AI.getType()); 0
2824 LLT IntPtrTy = getLLTForType(*IntPtrIRTy, *DL); 0
2825 if (MRI->getType(NumElts) != IntPtrTy) { 0
2826 Register ExtElts = MRI->createGenericVirtualRegister(IntPtrTy); 0
2827 MIRBuilder.buildZExtOrTrunc(ExtElts, NumElts); 0
2828 NumElts = ExtElts; 0
2829 } ----
2830 ----
2831 Type *Ty = AI.getAllocatedType(); 0
2832 ----
2833 Register AllocSize = MRI->createGenericVirtualRegister(IntPtrTy); 0
2834 Register TySize = ----
2835 getOrCreateVReg(*ConstantInt::get(IntPtrIRTy, DL->getTypeAllocSize(Ty))); 0
2836 MIRBuilder.buildMul(AllocSize, NumElts, TySize); 0
2837 ----
2838 // Round the size of the allocation up to the stack alignment size ----
2839 // by add SA-1 to the size. This doesn't overflow because we're computing ----
2840 // an address inside an alloca. ----
2841 Align StackAlign = MF->getSubtarget().getFrameLowering()->getStackAlign(); 0
2842 auto SAMinusOne = MIRBuilder.buildConstant(IntPtrTy, StackAlign.value() - 1); 0
2843 auto AllocAdd = MIRBuilder.buildAdd(IntPtrTy, AllocSize, SAMinusOne, 0
2844 MachineInstr::NoUWrap); 0
2845 auto AlignCst = ----
2846 MIRBuilder.buildConstant(IntPtrTy, ~(uint64_t)(StackAlign.value() - 1)); 0
2847 auto AlignedAlloc = MIRBuilder.buildAnd(IntPtrTy, AllocAdd, AlignCst); 0
2848 ----
2849 Align Alignment = std::max(AI.getAlign(), DL->getPrefTypeAlign(Ty)); 0
2850 if (Alignment <= StackAlign) 0
2851 Alignment = Align(1); 0
2852 MIRBuilder.buildDynStackAlloc(getOrCreateVReg(AI), AlignedAlloc, Alignment); 0
2853 ----
2854 MF->getFrameInfo().CreateVariableSizedObject(Alignment, &AI); 0
2855 assert(MF->getFrameInfo().hasVarSizedObjects()); 0
2856 return true; 0
2857 } ----
2858 ----
2859 bool IRTranslator::translateVAArg(const User &U, MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { 0
2860 // FIXME: We may need more info about the type. Because of how LLT works, ----
2861 // we're completely discarding the i64/double distinction here (amongst ----
2862 // others). Fortunately the ABIs I know of where that matters don't use va_arg ----
2863 // anyway but that's not guaranteed. ----
2864 MIRBuilder.buildInstr(TargetOpcode::G_VAARG, {getOrCreateVReg(U)}, 0
2865 {getOrCreateVReg(*U.getOperand(0)), 0
2866 DL->getABITypeAlign(U.getType()).value()}); 0
2867 return true; 0
2868 } ----

2870 bool IRTranslator::translateUnreachable(const User &U, MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { 0
2871 if (!MF->getTarget().Options.TrapUnreachable) 0
2872 return true; 0
2873 ----
2874 auto &UI = cast(U); 0
2875 // We may be able to ignore unreachable behind a noreturn call. ----
2876 if (MF->getTarget().Options.NoTrapAfterNoreturn) { 0
2877 const BasicBlock &BB = *UI.getParent(); 0
2878 if (&UI != &BB.front()) { 0
2879 BasicBlock::const_iterator PredI = ----
2880 std::prev(BasicBlock::const_iterator(UI)); 0
2881 if (const CallInst *Call = dyn_cast(&*PredI)) { 0
2882 if (Call->doesNotReturn()) 0
2883 return true; 0
2884 } ----
2885 } ----
2886 } ----
2887 ----
2888 MIRBuilder.buildIntrinsic(Intrinsic::trap, ArrayRef(), true); 0
2889 return true; 0
2890 } ----

2892 bool IRTranslator::translateInsertElement(const User &U, 0
2893 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
2894 // If it is a <1 x Ty> vector, use the scalar as it is ----
2895 // not a legal vector type in LLT. ----
2896 if (cast(U.getType())->getNumElements() == 1) 0
2897 return translateCopy(U, *U.getOperand(1), MIRBuilder); 0
2898 ----
2899 Register Res = getOrCreateVReg(U); 0
2900 Register Val = getOrCreateVReg(*U.getOperand(0)); 0
2901 Register Elt = getOrCreateVReg(*U.getOperand(1)); 0

2907 bool IRTranslator::translateExtractElement(const User &U, 0
2908 MachineIRBuilder &MIRBuilder) { ----
2909 // If it is a <1 x Ty> vector, use the scalar as it is ----
2910 // not a legal vector type in LLT. ----
2911 if (cast(U.getOperand(0)->getType())->getNumElements() == 1) 0
2912 return translateCopy(U, *U.getOperand(0), MIRBuilder); 0
2913 ----
2914 Register Res = getOrCreateVReg(U); 0
2915 Register Val = getOrCreateVReg(*U.getOperand(0)); 0
2916 const auto &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
2917 unsigned PreferredVecIdxWidth = TLI.getVectorIdxTy(*DL).getSizeInBits(); 0
2918 Register Idx; 0
2919 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast(U.getOperand(1))) { 0
2920 if (CI->getBitWidth() != PreferredVecIdxWidth) { 0
2921 APInt NewIdx = CI->getValue().zextOrTrunc(PreferredVecIdxWidth); 0
2922 auto *NewIdxCI = ConstantInt::get(CI->getContext(), NewIdx); 0
2923 Idx = getOrCreateVReg(*NewIdxCI); 0
2924 } 0
2925 } ----
2926 if (!Idx) 0
2927 Idx = getOrCreateVReg(*U.getOperand(1)); 0
2928 if (MRI->getType(Idx).getSizeInBits() != PreferredVecIdxWidth) { 0
2929 const LLT VecIdxTy = LLT::scalar(PreferredVecIdxWidth); 0
2930 Idx = MIRBuilder.buildZExtOrTrunc(VecIdxTy, Idx).getReg(0); 0
2931 } ----
2932 MIRBuilder.buildExtractVectorElement(Res, Val, Idx); 0
2933 return true; 0
2934 } ----

3087 void IRTranslator::finishPendingPhis() { 0
3088 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
3089 DILocationVerifier Verifier; 0
3090 GISelObserverWrapper WrapperObserver(&Verifier); 0
3091 RAIIDelegateInstaller DelInstall(*MF, &WrapperObserver); 0
3092 #endif // ifndef NDEBUG ----
3093 for (auto &Phi : PendingPHIs) { 0
3094 const PHINode *PI = Phi.first; 0
3095 ArrayRef ComponentPHIs = Phi.second; 0
3096 MachineBasicBlock *PhiMBB = ComponentPHIs[0]->getParent(); 0
3097 EntryBuilder->setDebugLoc(PI->getDebugLoc()); 0
3098 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
3099 Verifier.setCurrentInst(PI); 0
3100 #endif // ifndef NDEBUG ----
3101 ----
3102 SmallSet SeenPreds; 0
3103 for (unsigned i = 0; i < PI->getNumIncomingValues(); ++i) { 0
3104 auto IRPred = PI->getIncomingBlock(i); 0
3105 ArrayRef ValRegs = getOrCreateVRegs(*PI->getIncomingValue(i)); 0
3106 for (auto *Pred : getMachinePredBBs({IRPred, PI->getParent()})) { 0
3107 if (SeenPreds.count(Pred) || !PhiMBB->isPredecessor(Pred)) 0
3108 continue; 0
3109 SeenPreds.insert(Pred); 0
3110 for (unsigned j = 0; j < ValRegs.size(); ++j) { 0
3111 MachineInstrBuilder MIB(*MF, ComponentPHIs[j]); 0
3112 MIB.addUse(ValRegs[j]); 0
3113 MIB.addMBB(Pred); 0
3114 } ----
3115 } 0
3116 } ----
3117 } 0

3120 bool IRTranslator::translate(const Instruction &Inst) { 0
3121 CurBuilder->setDebugLoc(Inst.getDebugLoc()); 0
3122 CurBuilder->setPCSections(Inst.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_pcsections)); 0
3123 ----
3124 auto &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
3125 if (TLI.fallBackToDAGISel(Inst)) 0
3126 return false; 0
3127 ----
3128 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) { 0
3129 #define HANDLE_INST(NUM, OPCODE, CLASS) \ ----
3130 case Instruction::OPCODE: \ ----
3131 return translate##OPCODE(Inst, *CurBuilder.get()); ----
3132 #include "llvm/IR/Instruction.def" ----
3133 default: 0
3134 return false; 0
3135 } ----
3136 } ----
3137 ----
3138 bool IRTranslator::translate(const Constant &C, Register Reg) { 0
3139 // We only emit constants into the entry block from here. To prevent jumpy ----
3140 // debug behaviour remove debug line. ----
3141 if (auto CurrInstDL = CurBuilder->getDL()) 0
3142 EntryBuilder->setDebugLoc(DebugLoc()); 0
3143 ----
3144 if (auto CI = dyn_cast(&C)) 0
3145 EntryBuilder->buildConstant(Reg, *CI); 0
3146 else if (auto CF = dyn_cast(&C)) 0
3147 EntryBuilder->buildFConstant(Reg, *CF); 0
3148 else if (isa(C)) 0
3149 EntryBuilder->buildUndef(Reg); 0
3150 else if (isa(C)) 0
3151 EntryBuilder->buildConstant(Reg, 0); 0
3152 else if (auto GV = dyn_cast(&C)) 0
3153 EntryBuilder->buildGlobalValue(Reg, GV); 0
3154 else if (auto CAZ = dyn_cast(&C)) { 0
3155 if (!isa(CAZ->getType())) 0
3156 return false; 0
3157 // Return the scalar if it is a <1 x Ty> vector. ----
3158 unsigned NumElts = CAZ->getElementCount().getFixedValue(); 0
3159 if (NumElts == 1) 0
3160 return translateCopy(C, *CAZ->getElementValue(0u), *EntryBuilder); 0
3161 SmallVector Ops; 0
3162 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumElts; ++I) { 0
3163 Constant &Elt = *CAZ->getElementValue(I); 0
3164 Ops.push_back(getOrCreateVReg(Elt)); 0
3165 } ----
3166 EntryBuilder->buildBuildVector(Reg, Ops); 0
3167 } else if (auto CV = dyn_cast(&C)) { 0
3168 // Return the scalar if it is a <1 x Ty> vector. ----
3169 if (CV->getNumElements() == 1) 0
3170 return translateCopy(C, *CV->getElementAsConstant(0), *EntryBuilder); 0
3171 SmallVector Ops; 0
3172 for (unsigned i = 0; i < CV->getNumElements(); ++i) { 0
3173 Constant &Elt = *CV->getElementAsConstant(i); 0
3174 Ops.push_back(getOrCreateVReg(Elt)); 0
3175 } ----
3176 EntryBuilder->buildBuildVector(Reg, Ops); 0
3177 } else if (auto CE = dyn_cast(&C)) { 0
3178 switch(CE->getOpcode()) { 0
3179 #define HANDLE_INST(NUM, OPCODE, CLASS) \ ----
3180 case Instruction::OPCODE: \ ----
3181 return translate##OPCODE(*CE, *EntryBuilder.get()); ----
3182 #include "llvm/IR/Instruction.def" ----
3183 default: 0
3184 return false; 0
3185 } ----
3186 } else if (auto CV = dyn_cast(&C)) { 0
3187 if (CV->getNumOperands() == 1) 0
3188 return translateCopy(C, *CV->getOperand(0), *EntryBuilder); 0
3189 SmallVector Ops; 0
3190 for (unsigned i = 0; i < CV->getNumOperands(); ++i) { 0
3191 Ops.push_back(getOrCreateVReg(*CV->getOperand(i))); 0
3192 } ----
3193 EntryBuilder->buildBuildVector(Reg, Ops); 0
3194 } else if (auto *BA = dyn_cast(&C)) { 0
3195 EntryBuilder->buildBlockAddress(Reg, BA); 0
3196 } else ----
3197 return false; 0
3198 ----
3199 return true; 0
3200 } ----
3201 ----
3202 bool IRTranslator::finalizeBasicBlock(const BasicBlock &BB, 0
3203 MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { ----
3204 for (auto &BTB : SL->BitTestCases) { 0
3205 // Emit header first, if it wasn't already emitted. ----
3206 if (!BTB.Emitted) 0
3207 emitBitTestHeader(BTB, BTB.Parent); 0
3208 ----
3209 BranchProbability UnhandledProb = BTB.Prob; 0
3210 for (unsigned j = 0, ej = BTB.Cases.size(); j != ej; ++j) { 0
3211 UnhandledProb -= BTB.Cases[j].ExtraProb; 0
3212 // Set the current basic block to the mbb we wish to insert the code into ----
3213 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = BTB.Cases[j].ThisBB; 0
3214 // If all cases cover a contiguous range, it is not necessary to jump to ----
3215 // the default block after the last bit test fails. This is because the ----
3216 // range check during bit test header creation has guaranteed that every ----
3217 // case here doesn't go outside the range. In this case, there is no need ----
3218 // to perform the last bit test, as it will always be true. Instead, make ----
3219 // the second-to-last bit-test fall through to the target of the last bit ----
3220 // test, and delete the last bit test. ----
3221 ----
3222 MachineBasicBlock *NextMBB; ----
3223 if ((BTB.ContiguousRange || BTB.FallthroughUnreachable) && j + 2 == ej) { 0
3224 // Second-to-last bit-test with contiguous range: fall through to the ----
3225 // target of the final bit test. ----
3226 NextMBB = BTB.Cases[j + 1].TargetBB; 0
3227 } else if (j + 1 == ej) { 0
3228 // For the last bit test, fall through to Default. ----
3229 NextMBB = BTB.Default; 0
3230 } else { ----
3231 // Otherwise, fall through to the next bit test. ----
3232 NextMBB = BTB.Cases[j + 1].ThisBB; 0
3233 } ----
3234 ----
3235 emitBitTestCase(BTB, NextMBB, UnhandledProb, BTB.Reg, BTB.Cases[j], MBB); 0
3236 ----
3237 if ((BTB.ContiguousRange || BTB.FallthroughUnreachable) && j + 2 == ej) { 0
3238 // We need to record the replacement phi edge here that normally ----
3239 // happens in emitBitTestCase before we delete the case, otherwise the ----
3240 // phi edge will be lost. ----
3241 addMachineCFGPred({BTB.Parent->getBasicBlock(), 0
3242 BTB.Cases[ej - 1].TargetBB->getBasicBlock()}, 0
3243 MBB); ----
3244 // Since we're not going to use the final bit test, remove it. ----
3245 BTB.Cases.pop_back(); 0
3246 break; 0
3247 } ----
3248 } ----
3249 // This is "default" BB. We have two jumps to it. From "header" BB and from ----
3250 // last "case" BB, unless the latter was skipped. ----
3251 CFGEdge HeaderToDefaultEdge = {BTB.Parent->getBasicBlock(), 0
3252 BTB.Default->getBasicBlock()}; 0
3253 addMachineCFGPred(HeaderToDefaultEdge, BTB.Parent); 0
3254 if (!BTB.ContiguousRange) { 0
3255 addMachineCFGPred(HeaderToDefaultEdge, BTB.Cases.back().ThisBB); 0
3256 } ----
3257 } ----
3258 SL->BitTestCases.clear(); 0
3259 ----
3260 for (auto &JTCase : SL->JTCases) { 0
3261 // Emit header first, if it wasn't already emitted. ----
3262 if (!JTCase.first.Emitted) 0
3263 emitJumpTableHeader(JTCase.second, JTCase.first, JTCase.first.HeaderBB); 0
3264 ----
3265 emitJumpTable(JTCase.second, JTCase.second.MBB); 0
3266 } ----
3267 SL->JTCases.clear(); 0
3268 ----
3269 for (auto &SwCase : SL->SwitchCases) 0
3270 emitSwitchCase(SwCase, &CurBuilder->getMBB(), *CurBuilder); 0
3271 SL->SwitchCases.clear(); 0
3272 ----
3273 // Check if we need to generate stack-protector guard checks. ----
3274 StackProtector &SP = getAnalysis(); 0
3275 if (SP.shouldEmitSDCheck(BB)) { 0
3276 const TargetLowering &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
3277 bool FunctionBasedInstrumentation = ----
3278 TLI.getSSPStackGuardCheck(*MF->getFunction().getParent()); 0
3279 SPDescriptor.initialize(&BB, &MBB, FunctionBasedInstrumentation); 0
3280 } ----
3281 // Handle stack protector. ----
3282 if (SPDescriptor.shouldEmitFunctionBasedCheckStackProtector()) { 0
3283 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Unimplemented stack protector case\n"); 0
3284 return false; 0
3285 } else if (SPDescriptor.shouldEmitStackProtector()) { 0
3286 MachineBasicBlock *ParentMBB = SPDescriptor.getParentMBB(); 0
3287 MachineBasicBlock *SuccessMBB = SPDescriptor.getSuccessMBB(); 0
3288 ----
3289 // Find the split point to split the parent mbb. At the same time copy all ----
3290 // physical registers used in the tail of parent mbb into virtual registers ----
3291 // before the split point and back into physical registers after the split ----
3292 // point. This prevents us needing to deal with Live-ins and many other ----
3293 // register allocation issues caused by us splitting the parent mbb. The ----
3294 // register allocator will clean up said virtual copies later on. ----
3295 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SplitPoint = findSplitPointForStackProtector( 0
3296 ParentMBB, *MF->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo()); 0
3297 ----
3298 // Splice the terminator of ParentMBB into SuccessMBB. ----
3299 SuccessMBB->splice(SuccessMBB->end(), ParentMBB, SplitPoint, 0
3300 ParentMBB->end()); ----
3301 ----
3302 // Add compare/jump on neq/jump to the parent BB. ----
3303 if (!emitSPDescriptorParent(SPDescriptor, ParentMBB)) 0
3304 return false; 0
3305 ----
3306 // CodeGen Failure MBB if we have not codegened it yet. ----
3307 MachineBasicBlock *FailureMBB = SPDescriptor.getFailureMBB(); 0
3308 if (FailureMBB->empty()) { 0
3309 if (!emitSPDescriptorFailure(SPDescriptor, FailureMBB)) 0
3310 return false; 0
3311 } ----
3312 ----
3313 // Clear the Per-BB State. ----
3314 SPDescriptor.resetPerBBState(); 0
3315 } ----
3316 return true; 0
3317 } ----
3318 ----
3319 bool IRTranslator::emitSPDescriptorParent(StackProtectorDescriptor &SPD, 0
3320 MachineBasicBlock *ParentBB) { ----
3321 CurBuilder->setInsertPt(*ParentBB, ParentBB->end()); 0
3322 // First create the loads to the guard/stack slot for the comparison. ----
3323 const TargetLowering &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
3324 Type *PtrIRTy = Type::getInt8PtrTy(MF->getFunction().getContext()); 0
3325 const LLT PtrTy = getLLTForType(*PtrIRTy, *DL); 0
3326 LLT PtrMemTy = getLLTForMVT(TLI.getPointerMemTy(*DL)); 0
3327 ----
3328 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = ParentBB->getParent()->getFrameInfo(); 0
3329 int FI = MFI.getStackProtectorIndex(); 0
3330 ----
3331 Register Guard; 0
3332 Register StackSlotPtr = CurBuilder->buildFrameIndex(PtrTy, FI).getReg(0); 0
3333 const Module &M = *ParentBB->getParent()->getFunction().getParent(); 0
3334 Align Align = DL->getPrefTypeAlign(Type::getInt8PtrTy(M.getContext())); 0
3335 ----
3336 // Generate code to load the content of the guard slot. ----
3337 Register GuardVal = ----
3338 CurBuilder ----
3339 ->buildLoad(PtrMemTy, StackSlotPtr, 0
3340 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(*MF, FI), Align, 0
3341 MachineMemOperand::MOLoad | MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile) 0
3342 .getReg(0); 0

3345 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Stack protector xor'ing with FP not yet implemented"); 0
3346 return false; 0
3347 } ----
3348 ----

3350 if (const Function *GuardCheckFn = TLI.getSSPStackGuardCheck(M)) { 0

3352 // that needs this seems to be Windows, and we fall back on that currently. ----
3353 // The code still lives here in case that changes. ----
3354 // Silence warning about unused variable until the code below that uses ----
3355 // 'GuardCheckFn' is enabled. ----
3356 (void)GuardCheckFn; ----
3357 return false; 0
3358 #if 0 ----
3359 // The target provides a guard check function to validate the guard value. ----
3360 // Generate a call to that function with the content of the guard slot as ----
3361 // argument. ----
3362 FunctionType *FnTy = GuardCheckFn->getFunctionType(); ----
3363 assert(FnTy->getNumParams() == 1 && "Invalid function signature"); ----
3364 ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags; ----
3365 if (GuardCheckFn->hasAttribute(1, Attribute::AttrKind::InReg)) ----
3366 Flags.setInReg(); ----

3368 {GuardVal, FnTy->getParamType(0), {Flags}}); ----
3369 ----
3370 CallLowering::CallLoweringInfo Info; ----
3371 Info.OrigArgs.push_back(GuardArgInfo); ----
3372 Info.CallConv = GuardCheckFn->getCallingConv(); ----
3373 Info.Callee = MachineOperand::CreateGA(GuardCheckFn, 0); ----
3374 Info.OrigRet = {Register(), FnTy->getReturnType()}; ----
3375 if (!CLI->lowerCall(MIRBuilder, Info)) { ----
3376 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Failed to lower call to stack protector check\n"); ----
3377 return false; ----
3378 } ----
3379 return true; ----
3380 #endif ----
3381 } ----
3382 ----

3384 // Otherwise, emit a volatile load to retrieve the stack guard value. ----
3385 if (TLI.useLoadStackGuardNode()) { 0

3387 MRI->createGenericVirtualRegister(LLT::scalar(PtrTy.getSizeInBits())); 0
3388 getStackGuard(Guard, *CurBuilder); 0

3396 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(*MF, FI), Align, 0
3397 MachineMemOperand::MOLoad | 0
3398 MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile) ----
3399 .getReg(0); 0
3400 } ----
3401 ----
3402 // Perform the comparison. ----
3403 auto Cmp = ----
3404 CurBuilder->buildICmp(CmpInst::ICMP_NE, LLT::scalar(1), Guard, GuardVal); 0
3405 // If the guard/stackslot do not equal, branch to failure MBB. ----
3406 CurBuilder->buildBrCond(Cmp, *SPD.getFailureMBB()); 0
3407 // Otherwise branch to success MBB. ----
3408 CurBuilder->buildBr(*SPD.getSuccessMBB()); 0

3412 bool IRTranslator::emitSPDescriptorFailure(StackProtectorDescriptor &SPD, 0
3413 MachineBasicBlock *FailureBB) { ----
3414 CurBuilder->setInsertPt(*FailureBB, FailureBB->end()); 0
3415 const TargetLowering &TLI = *MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
3416 ----
3417 const RTLIB::Libcall Libcall = RTLIB::STACKPROTECTOR_CHECK_FAIL; 0
3418 const char *Name = TLI.getLibcallName(Libcall); 0
3419 ----
3420 CallLowering::CallLoweringInfo Info; 0
3421 Info.CallConv = TLI.getLibcallCallingConv(Libcall); 0
3422 Info.Callee = MachineOperand::CreateES(Name); 0
3423 Info.OrigRet = {Register(), Type::getVoidTy(MF->getFunction().getContext()), 0
3424 0}; 0
3425 if (!CLI->lowerCall(*CurBuilder, Info)) { 0
3426 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Failed to lower call to stack protector fail\n"); 0
3427 return false; 0
3428 } ----
3429 ----
3430 // On PS4/PS5, the "return address" must still be within the calling ----
3431 // function, even if it's at the very end, so emit an explicit TRAP here. ----
3432 // WebAssembly needs an unreachable instruction after a non-returning call, ----
3433 // because the function return type can be different from __stack_chk_fail's ----
3434 // return type (void). ----
3435 const TargetMachine &TM = MF->getTarget(); 0
3436 if (TM.getTargetTriple().isPS() || TM.getTargetTriple().isWasm()) { 0
3437 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Unhandled trap emission for stack protector fail\n"); 0
3438 return false; 0
3439 } ----
3440 return true; 0
3441 } 0
3442 ----
3443 void IRTranslator::finalizeFunction() { 0
3444 // Release the memory used by the different maps we ----
3445 // needed during the translation. ----
3446 PendingPHIs.clear(); 0
3447 VMap.reset(); 0
3448 FrameIndices.clear(); 0
3449 MachinePreds.clear(); 0
3450 // MachineIRBuilder::DebugLoc can outlive the DILocation it holds. Clear it ----
3451 // to avoid accessing free’d memory (in runOnMachineFunction) and to avoid ----
3452 // destroying it twice (in ~IRTranslator() and ~LLVMContext()) ----
3453 EntryBuilder.reset(); 0
3454 CurBuilder.reset(); 0
3455 FuncInfo.clear(); 0
3456 SPDescriptor.resetPerFunctionState(); 0
3457 } 0
3458 ----
3459 /// Returns true if a BasicBlock \p BB within a variadic function contains a ----
3460 /// variadic musttail call. ----
3461 static bool checkForMustTailInVarArgFn(bool IsVarArg, const BasicBlock &BB) { 0
3462 if (!IsVarArg) 0
3463 return false; 0
3464 ----
3465 // Walk the block backwards, because tail calls usually only appear at the end ----
3466 // of a block. ----
3467 return llvm::any_of(llvm::reverse(BB), [](const Instruction &I) { 0
3468 const auto *CI = dyn_cast(&I); 0
3469 return CI && CI->isMustTailCall(); 0
3470 }); 0
3471 } ----
